column8:
Juarez's Martial Arts  for Concentration is not just another after-school activity. Basketball, soccer, and baseball are all great activities for children, but Juarez's Martial Arts is personal development through a physical discipline. Our exciting, yet disciplined classes focus a child's attention, thus improving his or her ability to learn. Learning builds a sense of accomplishment. With each new accomplishment a student's self-confidence grows, and confidence is the first step in the empowerment of a young person's physical and mental abilities.

Once we begin to develop a student's self confidence, we are then able to install the values of respect, courtesy, honesty, perseverance, and integrity that are the foundation of martial arts, dating back thousands of years. Your child will develop perseverance, which is a non-quitting spirit to overcome life's obstacles. Instilling a non-quitting spirit helps a child overcome challenges, to succeed in the face of adversity, and to be a goal setter and a goal getter!

Z-Ultimate Self Defense Studios, LLC – ZUSDS – is a part of a family of martial arts companies formed with one goal in mind – to
 provide “Z-Ultimate” martial arts experience for students and their 
families by providing life changing and character building experiences 
through world-class personalized martial arts instruction. It is the largest martial arts company of its kind, with locations in the Midwest and on the West Coast.
What is unique about Z-USDS – besides it’s Dynamic Mastery Method™ of
 instruction – is that it is NOT just an association or license, where 
any martial artist can pay a small fee and use the rights to the logo 
and attain certification. There are many such organizations that boast 
hundreds, even thousands of members with this model.
With a philosophy of leadership that teaches, “Be a product of what 
you represent”, every single staff and support member of the Z-USDS 
family are martial artists and train actively. By doing so, we never are
 “out of touch” with what is happening in our locations because we are 
students, too.

The USSD system of self-defense is uniquely organized and you will learn;More than 120 kicking techniquesOver 300 hand strikesMore than 100 pressure points30 different stances6 different blocking systems38 practice forms108 defenses against club attacks, knives, and gunsPractice drills to hone your defensive skillsUSSD
 instructors are expertly trained in our proprietary system of 
self-defense based on the practices of Shaolin’s warrior monks. Using 
well tested teaching methods ensures that you and your family will have a
 positive experience learning and practicing self-defense skills that 
will be effective if needed.

The Modesto Boxing 
Gym is dedicated to providing youth of the community an organization 
which instills sportsmanship, fairplay, physical conditioning, and 
mental, spiritual and emotional health. Boxers develop self confidence 
and self esteem while learning Boxing skills and self defense. The 
importance of education is stressed. Many of our participants are 
considered at-risk youth.

These virtues are instilled by the 
coaches and board members in the training of the youth and in the boxing
 programs.  The objective is to promote and develop amateur boxing for 
the benefits of amateur boxers of all ages and abilities, in accordance 
with the standard under the rules prescribed by the United States of 
America Amateur Boxing Federation, Inc.  (U.S.A./A.B.F.) and the local 
Boxing Committee. Our efforts will be phenomenal, with our boxers 
qualifying and competing and winning at national levels.

REDLANDS
 KARATE CLUB is dedicated to serving the youth in Redlands and the
surrounding communities. Our instructors have many years of training in 
the martial arts and are looking forward to passing that knowledge on to
 the youth of Redlands. ﻿
﻿
Don’t get hit—Don’t hit 

We devote ourselves to
spreading Karate-do with the world-wide
view, we cultivate and
develop our physical strength and
spiritual health
by studying and training for that purpose. 
 
We will always devote ourselves to training based on these five precepts:
Teachers and students relate to each other on the
basis of loyalty and honor
Love and respect your mother and father
Respect seniors
Sincerity to friends
Affection for juniors

column1: The Little Gym of San Jose (South)
column8:
With more than 300 locations across the globe, The Little Gym is the 
worldʼs premier experiential learning and physical development center 
for kids ages four months through 12 years. Each week, progressively 
structured classes and a positive learning environment create 
opportunities for your child to try new things and build 
self-confidence, all with a grin that stretches from ear to ear.
At The Little Gym of San Jose (South), our environment is fun, but 
our purpose is serious. For more than 35 years, our trained instructors 
have nurtured happy, confident kids through a range of programs 
including parent/child classes, gymnastics, karate, dance and sports 
skills development, plus enjoyable extras like camps, Parentsʼ Survival 
Nights and Awesome Birthday Bashes. In all of our programs, physical 
activity is a conduit for Three-Dimensional Learning. In every 
dimension, self-confidence and a proud smile are evident outcomes.

column1: Happy Ocean Tai Chi Kung Fu Academy
column8:
Applying his 
more than 40 years of study in the martial arts, Master Yeung has 
combined his extensive knowledge into a comprehensive, easy to 
understand exercise system. His system of teaching is unique because he 
shows his students how Tai Chi builds on 12 circular movements and 13 
components. It is based on what he has found to be most effective over 
the years that he has been studying, practicing and teaching Tai Chi. 
Chi Kung exercises round out the system for maximum health benefits. The
 Happy Ocean Tai Chi program encompasses breathing techniques, balance, 
understanding Yin Yan, forms for practice, equipment for strengthening 
and improving skills, and using everyday, common objects as weapons for 
self defense. Learning this Tai Chi and Chi Kung program will harmonize 
your Mind, Body, and Spirit.

Founder Clint Robinson left the U.S. Air Force after serving his 
country including duty in South Korea, where he discovered the positive 
values and healthy fitness derived from training in Taekwondo martial 
arts. Returning to the United States, Mr. Robinson came west to settle 
in Sacramento, CA, where he opened his first Taekwondo training school 
on Broadway.
Founded in 1975 on the principles of teaching excellence, personal 
attention and tradition, for more than 40 years, Robinson’s Taekwondo 
provides you with the most complete and effective methods to reach your 
full potential.
While self-defense techniques are often the first thought in choosing
 Taekwondo as a martial art, most students quickly discover the healthy 
fitness, positive attitudes and mental sharpness that come from physical
 training. Both adults and children benefit by controlling weight, 
increasing strength, endurance and flexibility while gaining confidence 
from achieving greater respect for themselves and others.

column1: Kovar's Satori Academy of Martial Arts
column8:
In 1978, Kyoshi or “Master Teacher” Dave Kovar opened his first 
school with a vision to empower people by teaching martial arts on a 
completely different level than could be found anywhere else.  His 
brother Tim, who brought innovative business practice to the operation, 
soon joined him.
The brothers’ reputation for combining self-defense and life skills 
grew.  As the word spread, the Kovar’s opened new locations, garnered 
awards, earned prestigious industry accolades, and gained national 
recognition.

We are an independent family owned full-time Fitness & Kickboxing center focusing on fitness, personal protection skills, true self-esteem and sincere character development for children, teens and adults.
Serving Sonoma County since 1992, we offer a variety of fitness 
options at reasonable rates. Our Kickboxing curriculum is age specific 
and functionally relevant for every age group. We place a high emphasis 
on providing our members with physical benefits that are matched by equally important mental skills.

HMA has grown into a one stop shop for the health and skill driven 
individual. Now after 10 years, HMA provides a variety of activities for
 all ages. All fantastic for better health and personal growth, the 
logical convenience is customer friendly.

The goals of HMA are simple. To give everyone the ability to receive 
instruction with integrity and transparency, offering flexible choices 
with personable dispositions highlights our unique difference.

 The owner believes that Martial Arts, Health and Fitness should not be a market but a way of life. Ethical and Moral business practice along with unwavering personal standards are essential for long term stability and
 growth. HMA respectfully considers itself a school by making standards 
and integrity its highest priority.

Specializing  in the Traditional and Spiritual forms of Northern Shaolin, Tai Chi Praying 
        Mantis, Seven Star Praying Mantis, Plum Flower Praying Mantis, the Eighteen 
        Classical Weapons, Yang, Chen & Wu Tai Chi Chuan, Baguazhang, Hsing 
        Yi, Internal Chi Kung & Nei Gung methods of Wudang and Shaolin, and 
        the Five Families Choi, Lee, Fut, Mok, Hung Five Animal Snake, Tiger, 
        Crane, Dragon, Leopard forms of the Southern Fist. Lion & Dragon Dance 
        of both Northern & Southern Lineage.

Studying at Pitts’ Martial Arts benefits your entire family with:
 Increased Self-Confidence
 Stress Relief
 Sharper Discipline
 Rich Cultural Experiences
 Outlets for Excess Energy
 Improved Concentration
 Self Defense Training
 Reduced Shyness in Children

Tucked away on the corner of Delaware and Swift, Kaijin Mixed Martial 
Arts offers one-of-a-kind personal training with some of the best in the
 business. With world-renowned instructors Garth Taylor (winner of 
multiple Brazilian Jiu Jitsu world championships), Clement Shields, and 
Sam Radetsky, you can be sure you’re training with a master. The studio 
offers Brazilian Jiu Jitsu, kickboxing, boxing, and Judo in classes 
tailored to all ages in a comfortable and friendly environment. Kaijin 
is a top-notch gym that can help improve even the most advanced 
students.

We follow the principles and philosophy as set forth by the Founder of 
Matsubayashi Ryu ,  Shoshin Nagamine Sensei. He fervently believes that 
the dojo is the place where courage is fostered and superior human 
nature is bred through the ecstacy of sweating in hard work. It is the 
sacred place where the human spirit is polished.

Moore’s Shou Shu is an application art. We use the fighting styles of 
seven different animals to develop fighting skills. It’s called an 
application art because we have eliminated all the wasted motion and 
teach the self-defense application part of the technique. The term Shou 
Shu means “Fighting ways of the beast” or “Beast Art”.
 The benefits 
that are attained by training in Shou Shu are; increased 
self-confidence, improved physical fitness, increased concentration, 
discipline, flexibility, Positive reactions in self-defense situation, 
etc.

Aikido is a non-competitive martial art.  There are no tournaments or
 competitions.  Learning is by repetitive practice of movements and 
techniques with a partner.
                Aikido of Santa Barbara is a 501c3 non-profit 
organization whose mission is to enhance the physical, mental, and 
spiritual health of youth and families by cultivating their minds and 
bodies through the knowledge and practice of the traditional Japanese 
art of Aikido.
                Aikido of Santa Barbara teaches a non-competitive, 
non-combative physical art that places emphasis on 
non-violent resolution, tolerance of others, and overall social harmony,
 Aikido of Santa Barbara programs serve to enhance the
 quality of life for those participating, and enable the dojo to cater 
to the diversity of the community. Sponsors, such as The Balm 
Foundation, help to make this happen by underwriting programs like the 
Santa Barbara Junior High Aikido Class.

In all classes we teach our students about being aware of their 
surroundings and what to do "IF".  They will also be learning 
traditional Shorin Ryu karate and Aikido, as a base, along 
with effective techniques from other styles to help defend themselves 
against armed and unarmed assailants.  We always stress the importance 
of safety and using what they've learned for self-defense only.

All students will attain belt ranks through individual testing according to their individual abilities and of equal importance their all-around attitude in and out of the dojo

home of JJ Machado Black belt Matt Baker. Jean Jacques machado jiu jitsu
 competition team. Offering classes 7 days a week, day and night. 2 
locations, southwest and northwest Bakersfield. Kids to adults. Stop by 
for a free class. cheers and GWG.

Koryo Family Taekwondo Center is a black belt school dedicated to 
tradition, discipline, respect, and excellence.  Our goal is to help our
 students become better people through martial arts.  For children, this
 means becoming a better student, son, or daughter by learning courtesy,
 integrity, perseverance, self-control, indomitable spirit, and winning 
positive attitude.
Our curriculum is comprehensive, giving the student a rounded 
perspective on martial arts.  Students twelve years of age or under have
 four areas to learn, while teens and adults have five.  These areas 
include martial arts knowledge, board breaking skills, arranged 
defensive techniques, forms routine, and self-defense (teens/adults 
only).  Once they have learned the various areas and have met their 
attendance requirements, they become eligible to test for belt 
promotion.

Our ATA Martial Arts Centers are the top rated martial arts schools in 
the Oxnard community. We offer programs to all ages and fitness levels. 
Give us a call and experience the difference martial arts can make on 
you or your child’s life.

Combined Martial Science (CMS) has one of the largest mixed martial arts programs in the Inland Empire. Located in Chino, California, we have 
been dedicated to making our students' martial arts experience enjoyable
 and satisfying for over 25 years. Although we honor martial arts 
traditions that go back centuries, we utilize a dynamic teaching style 
and are constantly seeking new and innovative ways to motivate and 
excite our students.
At Combined Martial Science, we take pride in developing our students on 
an individual basis. We understand that each student possesses unique 
skills and talents, and we thrive on bringing out those skills in all of
 our students. By using a variety of training methods and programs, we 
are able to build strong minds and even stronger bodies. Serving as a 
positive role model is a responsibility that we at CMS take very 
seriously.

Welcome to Okinawa-Te Karate. Our goal is to instill self confidence, 
honesty, courage and character.  We develop self defense skills, 
strength and coordination.  We are serious about martial arts.  Self 
Defense is Common Sense!

We are a training facility dedicated to extend the teachings of the ancient Shaolin martial arts. Shaolin Kung Fu was originated
 by the Shaolin monks of China and is renowned for its defensive 
mechanisms and intricate animal forms. The art has created elaborate 
emphasis on flexibility, strength, agility, speed, coordination, and 
grace. Shaolin Kung Fu is an exemplification of character, discipline, 
and total well-being.
 
 U.S. SHAOLIN KUNG FU's curriculum and 
instructors are devoted to equipping its students with influential 
concepts such as respect, character-building, motivation, cooperation, 
physical exercise, and increased mental acuity.

Through high quality martial arts instruction, we empower people of all ages to achieve their full potential.
By emphasizing self-defense, health, fitness and life skills in a
 friendly, safe, positive environment,we inspire our students to become 
more confident, successful, contributing members of our community.

EMA provides a safe, fun environment for all students and parents. To 
ensure the most realistic self defense training available. And to 
continually re-enforce life lessons to all students, young and old.

The Christian Karate Federation is a ministry designed to use martial arts to create opportunities for Christian leaders to both minister to Christians and to witness to non-believers and affect them with the gospel of Jesus Christ. The purpose of this ministry is to ultimately produce the fruit of the Spirit and Christ-likeness in all those involved. * Colossians 3:17 - And whatever you do, whether in word or deed, do it all in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks to the Father through Him.*I Timothy 4:8 - For physical training is of some value, but godliness has value for all things, holding promise for both the present life and the life to come.

Olympian Tae Kwon Do Center Training Program is based on Traditional and Olympic Style Tae Kwon Do.
Through years of accumulated teaching experience, Master Carlos Hernandez has developed a
program that is easy to follow and assimilate regardless you are a kid 
or an adult.
WHO SAID THAT TAE KWON DO WAS NOT SUPPOSED TO BE FUN?
Even though each group is under a different teaching system, our classes are designed for
our kids to learn and have fun at the same time.  (The Kids program is 
based in games and challenges that help them to interact with the group 
and gradually adapt to the hard work.  They are systematically 
introduced to the program and eventually to discipline.  Your kid(s) 
doesn't know that he/she is working our!  They are just having lots of 
fun!)

column1: Le Blanc's Kickboxing and Taekwondo Center
column8:
Le Blanc's Kickboxing and Taekwondo Center has been offering instruction
 and training in Taekwondo since 1984. Located in La Mesa, CA,    Le 
Blanc's Kickboxing and Taekwondo Center has produced champions in life 
as well as in the martial arts.  

Headed by Paul Le Blanc (Grandmaster, Certified Instructor, 10Th Degree Black Belt) and a staff
of expert instructors and managers Miguel Carrasco, Mallory 
Albrecht,Lori Ferrigno, Nathan Walker, Ty McGowan, Maryann Le 
Blanc, Michael Ferrigno, Steve Mangan, Kaya Todd. Le Blanc's Kickboxing 
and Taekwondo Center offers a number of programs for physical fitness 
and instruction in Taekwondo, Kickboxing, karate, MMA, jujitsu, tiny 
tigers, kids karate, family martial arts, practical self defense, body 
conditioning and core work outs.

Blue Dragon Taekwondo Academy is a community of 
committed and positive martial arts instructors and students who are 
striving to improve the physical, mental and social aspects of their 
lives. We work together to help everyone achieve their goals and become 
the best they are capable of becoming.
Those who choose to train at Blue Dragon Taekwondo Academy
have a desire to achieve a high standard of excellence in all aspects 
of their lives and are willing to commit to constant improvement.
Our martial arts instructors work to further develop this desire to 
improve in our students by getting them to set personal goals so their 
motivation to excel comes from within. To us, this is truly the best 
form of leadership.
We are black belt martial artists who stand tall and live strong. That’s what sets us — and our students — apart from the crowd.

Shaolin Temple USA is the first official North American branch of the world famous Songshan Shaolin Temple in Henan Province of China, the original Shaolin Temple established in 495 AD. Songshan Shaolin Temple is the birthplace of Chinese Chan (Zen) Buddhism and Shaolin Kung Fu.
                                                        
Under the direction of Founder and Executive Director Master Shi YanRan—34th generation Shaolin Temple Buddhist Monk, a team of Shaolin Temple Warrior Monks is stationed at Shaolin Temple USA to
 carry on the 1,500-year old traditions and training disciplines of 
Shaolin Temple. Their mission is to share Shaolin culture with the 
American people. Shaolin Temple USA teaches Shaolin Kung Fu Chan (Zen) through the disciplines of Shaolin Kung Fu and Qigong.

The greatest gift you can give your child is confidence!  Here at The 
Little Gym of Fresno we  help kids between the ages of 4 months and 12 
years grow physically, emotionally, and socially! Call for a free 
introductory class today!

Claudio Franca Academy brings you Brazilian Jiu Jitsu for competition, 
self-defense, fitness and family fun. Brazilian Jiu JItsu is a lifestyle
 come join us and let Jiu Jitsu make your life even better! Also join us
 for Muay Thai with Ryan "T2" Roy

To transmit the system of Aikido in a way that 
encourages self realization. To provide a safe place to be challenged, 
explore and learn. To help others gain martial knowledge and abilityDescriptionAikido of Fresno is a dedicated Aikido Dojo offering over 17 hours of training each week.

column1: Tae Ryong Tae Kwon Do School
column8:
Established in 1982, Tae Ryong Taekwondo School - Camarillo was the 
FIRST Taekwondo School in Ventura County. When Grand Master Shin first 
arrived to the United States he only knew Koreatown in Los Angeles. One 
day he got lost on the highway and found himself in the beautiful City 
of Camarillo. He knew this was the perfect place to plant roots for what
would grow to be Tae Ryong Taekwondo School.

Today, Tae Ryong - Camarillo is 5,000 square feet and is "The place for 
Martial Arts in Camarillo". There are 2 training floors, Tiger Room and 
Dragon Room, fully equipped and padded for safety, so it can accommodate
 hundreds of students in a class period. Centrally located in Camarillo 
on Pickwick Dr. and Arniel Rd., Tae Ryong Taekwondo School has taught 
over 60,000 Children and Adults at this one location alone.

Our school is dedicated to build a strong community one black belt at a 
time.  We do this by developing students with healthy minds and strong 
bodies, and the ability to defend themselves and loved ones.  We empower
 our students with important values including courtesy, respect, 
patience, confidence, self-esteem, positive attitude and indomitable 
spirit.  We are committed to constantly improving our service to our 
students through continually educating and training our professional 
team of instructors.  Through this constant and never ending attitude of
 improvement you can be assured you are a part of a team that is on a 
quest to be the very best.

Traditional Okinawan Karate - self defense for all ages. Family style - 
everyone welcome! Located inside Delta Valley Athletic Club - do not 
have to be a gym member to join this karate school.

Sensei Geng Arceo is the Chief Instructor of Arceo's Shotokan Karate.
 He holds the rank of 5th degree black belt in Shotokan karate. He 
started karate at the age of 7 in 1973. He trained under the instruction
 of his older brother Sensei Augusto Arceo who is under the school of 
Beaux's Brother Karate Association. Sensei Augusto Arceo first 
introduced Sensei Geng Arceo to Martial Arts tournaments in the late 
70's. In 1990, ARCEO'S SHOTOKAN KARATE was established by Sensei Geng 
Arceo. He first brought all his students to compete and try traditional 
karate tournaments. For many years, all the Arceo's Shotokan Karate 
students had all their shares of winning their gold medals. In the mid 
90's, Sensei Arceo started bringing his students to compete in all the 
open Sport Martial Arts tournaments.   That was the start of producing local Champions, National Champions, and World Champions.  Arceo's Shotokan Karate is well known in the Bay Area because of what they have
accomplished, and in how they train in Traditional techniques with 
modern approaches of every movement.

column1: Simon Rhee Tae Kwon Do Training Center
column8:
Master Simon Rhee, 7th Degree Black Belt, Martial Artist, Stuntman, 
Stunt Coordinator, Celebrity Instructor for the Entertainment Industry.

Welcome to Black Belt Academy(Martial Arts school). We have been 
training sharing the benefits of martial arts with Laguna Hills, Laguna 
Niguel, Aliso Viejo, Mission Viejo for over five years. Our state of the
art training center provides the perfect backdrop for developing the 
skill and determination needed to succeed in martial arts. Black Belt 
Academy is staffed by professional, experienced, instructors,
who have dedicated their lives to sharing the power of martial arts 
with the community. All of our instructors are certified black belts, 
with over than 20 years of training experience. We offer many classes to
accommodate your busy schedule. Regardless of your age or level of 
experience, we have a program that is tailored just for you.
 At Black Belt Academy, we not only teach technique, we build character 
through inner-strength, courage, vision, respect, and discipline. 
The spiritual side of martial arts is not ignored.
Come in for a free tour! We offer a patient, supportive atmosphere. All ages welcome!

The most athletic of martial arts, Taekwondo offers students much more 
than   physical fitness. This ancient art is based ontechniques 
developed 2000 years   ago and teaches and fosters self-confidence, 
respect self-defense, energy and   pride. US Taekwondo Team develops 
personality and character that is directed   toward the attachment inner
 peace and tranquility. The martial arts develop   physical and mental 
coordination and relaxation. The training exercises involve   the entire
 body promoting fitness good health, flexibility and agility.   
Originating from Korea, Taekwondo translates as the "art of hand and 
foot   techniques.YOU CAN LEARN REAL TAEKWONDO AT TRADITIONAL TAEKWONDO SCHOOL ONLY.

Bell’s Kenpo Karate is an independent school, not affiliated with any other local schools. We are directly connected with the Rich 
Hale and the Ohana Kenpo Karate Association.
At Bells’ Kenpo Karate, training takes place in a formal atmosphere with an emphasis on etiquette and self-control as well as physical ability and coordination.Kenpo Karate as taught by Fred and Connie Bell teaches self-defense and self-control through three primary methods:
Basics
Katas (forms)
Sparring
Basics focus on various striking, blocking, and kicking exercises that build proper form and technique.
Katas teach focus, concentration, mental discipline and practical self -defense against single and multiple attackers.
Sparring builds reflex, timing and spontaneous reaction without knowing your opponent’s attack.
Above all, Kenpo Karate teaches the practitioner to be the best person they can be through self-discipline, self-confidence and self-respect.

Oshiro Dojo, in San Mateo, California, is the world headquarters (honbu)
of the Ryukyu Bujutsu Kenkyu Doyukai (RBKD), an international organization
chartered by Sensei Chogi Kishaba for the study and development of 
traditional Okinawan martial arts.
                
RBKD Chief Instructor (Shihan) Toshihiro Oshiro is a native Okinawan who has been teaching karate and
kobujutsu in the San Francisco Bay area since 1978. Shihan Oshiro is a widely recognized authority on the history and techniques of traditional
Okinawan martial arts. He and his dojo are dedicated to the study and
teaching of Shima-Ha Shorin-ryu karate and Yamanni-ryu kobujutsu.
Oshiro Dojo has classes for adults and children of all ages.Beginners and experienced martial artists alike are
welcome to join the dojo at any time, and visitors are also welcome to watch classes.

The Pure Shaolin Kung Fu Academy teaches the Chinese arts of Kung Fu,
 Tai Chi and other physical forms that generate constructive energy for 
harmony of the body, the spirit and the world.  In these arts, 
the important point is that the mind is not separate from the body.  How
 one moves and behaves in physical ways can affect and enhance how one 
can build a healthy lifestyle.  Pure Shaolin Kung Fu Academy was founded in 2004 with the primary focus on Northern Shaolin Kung Fu.
Today, we have grown into a sports academy with many diverse goals:
Offer a variety of programs for all ages and skill levels from beginners to advance.Provide a comprehensive  experience for all of our students to obtain their lifelong benefits.Provide a positive learning experience helping our students achieve their full potential.Promoting cultural exchange between China and the United States.Provide the public with authentic instructors for Chinese Martial Arts classes.Training the Wushu teams for national and/or international competitions and serving as a resource center for our students.Provide educational opportunities for coaches and judges to study physical education in China.

White Tiger Kung Fu is martial arts school in Los Angeles, California 
offering training in both Kung Fu and Qigong for all ages 6 and up.  
First class is free and we welcome new students of all levels.

The mission of Force 1 Shotokan is to build a community of people striving to develop a strong body and a healthy mind. Our program teaches effective self-defense in a fun and encouraging environment while instilling 
the life skills and character of a true martial artist.
                        
Values such as integrity, patience, self control and respect enable our students to achieve a positive attitude, confidence, high self esteem and a healthy spirit. These values and life skills will lead 
to outstanding improvements in academics, careers, physical fitness, mental health and relationships.
                        
Though the art and techniques are traditional, the teaching method has been 
 modernized with fast paced background music and positive personal 
reinforcement. The atmosphere in the dojo is warm but serious; 
"We will have fun, and learn more doing it." When people enter the dojo, they get a feeling this is a serious but positive pla It is not about training hard, it is about the quality of training. Force 1 Shotokan 
Karate is one of a very small number of Karate schools in the valley to have coached and trained students to become consistent winners.

The Cassio Werneck Brazilian Jiu Jitsu Academy is the premier BJJ school
 in all of Sacramento. Cassio is the most decorated and accomplished BJJ
 athlete in the entire area. Our school is over 7,000 square feet and 
has three mats for various programs. We also have a CrossFit area that 
is constantly improving.

Character Cultivating, Discipline Developing, 
Powerful, Exciting, Engaging, 
Parent Boosting Martial Arts Program 
Ph.D. Designed and Master Made for Kids

Pro-Am Family Training Center is dedicated to enriching the lives of 
each and every member by providing energetic and innovative classes for 
everyone in your family. What makes our school unique and different from
 any other martial arts school is our age appropriate curriculum 
designed to challenge all of our students, whatever your skill level may
 be. Pro-Am prides itself on putting your family first, which is why we 
strive to keep a family friendly atmosphere at our school, while 
providing hands on training that promotes personal development and 
enhancement of one’s personal safety.

column1: Choi's Institute of Tae Kwon Do
column8:
Choi's Institute of Tae Kwon Do  has been established and teaching traditional Tae
Kwon Do in San Jose for over 40 years!  Grand Master Choi is the only Grand Master
in the Evergreen area to reach 9th degree black belt certification from Korea (Kukkiwon,World Taekwondo Headquarters).
We offer classes for children, teens and adults, ranging
from basic to advanced. Classes combine learning and practicing Tae Kwon Do, with
stretching and physical/aerobic conditioning.  At higher levels students will learn
to fight using light contact.  Fighting (also known as sparring) is closely supervised
and requires the students to wear protective equipment.  Protective equipment may
be purchased directly through Choi's studio.

Pacific Alliance of Martial Arts (P.A.M.A.) teaches 
Tae Kwon Do and Filipino Martial Arts. We teach classes for men, women, 
and children. It's great discipline! Children learn respect, 
self-confidence, concentration, and develop strong leadership skills. 
At Pacific Alliance of Martial Arts, students learn 
self-defense of the body and of the mind. Students learn to be well balanced 
physically, mentally, and spiritually. Martial Arts training is beneficial 
to everyone. It takes patience, commitment, and goal-setting.

Although our techniques are based on centuries old 
knowledge, our applications of that knowledge sets Martial Arts America 
apart from the other schools.  We realize that each student possesses 
different physical abilities.  Size and strength varies with each 
individual, so once you have acquired a strong foundation in the basics, our 
program will enhance your personal physical capabilities and maximize your 
self defense skills.  You will understand exactly what it takes, 
mentally and physically, to defend yourself or your loved ones should the 
need ever arise.

Red Dragon Karate is the original mixed martial art.  Our classes 
include martial arts from the seven eastern regions that gave birth to 
the martial arts:  Japan, China, Korea, Okinawa, Indonesia, Philippines,
and Tibet.  From these areas our founder included arts that

Muay Thai or Thai Boxingï¿½was born on 
the battlefields of the 15th century, during the legendary clashes 
between Thai (or Siamese) armies and their bitter rivals, the Burmese. 
Trained in the weapons-based fighting method known as Krabi Krabong, 
these early Thai soldiers also became famous for their toughness in 
close-quarters weaponless combat, where legs, knees, elbows and hands 
took the place of swords and sticks. This type of weaponless fighting 
became Muay Thai, known as the ï¿½Science of Eight Limbs. ï¿½Though the Thai army still uses its lethal techniques, Muay Thai has also been the countryï¿½s most popular spectator sport for hundreds of years. There 
are more than 65,000 professional Muay Thai fighters in Thailand today. 
Many of them are poor peasants who begin training when they are as young
as six years old, studying with highly respected teachers and risking 
injury or worse for the chance to compete.

Today there is a trend in the martial arts toward mixed arts, that is, 
wrestling has been added to the traditional stand-up arts, but it seems as though the arts have lost the positiveness that they always have conveyed!  Here at UMAA we believe the art should give you strength, 
balance, coordination, fitness, and a positive self-attitude.
We haven’t changed the art to comply with a fad, it is the original art,
started 527 AD in China.  It incorporates five main animals as part of 
fighting techniques. The tiger, leopard, crane, snake, and dragon 
techniques allow you to overcome any opponent.  It’s similar to the game
“rocks, paper, and scissors”, in that if someone large is coming 
directly at you, he may be considered the tiger. You will know from your
studies how to defend against this with crane, snake and leopard 
techniques! You’ll get in great shape while learning self-defense and you’ll enjoy it!

Sifu Kong started studying martial arts when he was 6 years old in his 
native Hong Kong. Two years later, he began studying Hung Gar with Lam Jo, providing a direct link to the origins of Hung Gar and to the famous Wong Fei ­Hung, popularized in such movies as Drunken Master  and Once 
Upon a Time in China.
In 1977, Kong moved to Los Angeles with his wife Nancy and three children, 
Andrew, Angela and Annice and opened his school in Hollywood. His students 
have gone on to continue Kong's teachings and today his Siu Lum Pai 
Association spans from the original school in Hawaii to Los Angeles, Utah, 
Texas, Oklahoma, Mexico and Germany. Kong travels continuously to teach his 
art to students of the Sui Lum Pai Kung Fu Association Schools worldwide.
Kong has been featured in the magazines of Black Belt, Inside Kung Fu 
and Karate Illustrated . In 1974, he was inducted into the Black Belt Hall of Fame

talents of all students and to instill in them the desire to be the best
martial artist possible, while not sacrificing the high degree of respect and
humbleness expected within the martial arts. 
Furthermore, UMAC promotes karate as self-defense, not aggression.  This is based upon the traditional “Dojo
Kun” or code, which states that the true martial artist should:
Seekperfection of character, intraining the mind and spirit;Be faithful, to oneself, as well as the Sensei and other teachers;Endeavor, to always do one’s best;Respect others, as well as strive to be
respected;Refrain from violent behavior, for the practice of karate is to defend, not to be
the aggressor.

The philosophy of Taekwondo has been passed on from Master to students for several thousand years, each interpreting and 
applying that knowledge to his or her way of life and teaching.
Philosophy as Master Steinhauser has been instructed and as he now instructs his students can be best defined as 
"an overall vision of, or an attitude toward life and the purpose of life."  A search for inner peace and strength
by learning to control the emotions and conquer fear, anger, and hatred.
Taekwondo teaches that clear and organized mind projects a stronger, self-controlled, secure individual.  By seeking harmony with his or her surroundings, a Taekwondo person will leave behind abusive aggression and violence, to become a calm and caring human being.
In summary, the philosophy of Taekwondo is the understanding of oneself and others, respect for all living things and 
loyalty of country, family, Master, teachers, and friends.
Taekwondo is a way of life.

column1: United States Academy of Martial Arts
column8:
At the United States Academy of Martial Arts, our “Do-jo” (The place of the “Way” or “Path”) involves a journey of three steps:
1st Step:  We believe in “Power Under Control”.   The more powerful a 
martial artist, the more important it is to find balance by embodying 
great character traits.  The first step in the martial arts journey is 
to gain control of oneself.
2nd Step:  Skill development starts with
respectful, attentive, and determined teachers and students.  Skill 
development grows into the ability to apply athletic attributes to the 
learned techniques.  
3rd Step:  Once the techniques become 
instinctive, the martial arts journey re-born again through teaching 
others and giving back to the art.  A martial arts leader is born.  
During this step, and through developing others, a student becomes a 
martial arts expert.

Kukkido Martial Arts offers a comprehensive martial arts training system that teaches different techniques from Taekwondo, Aikido, Cardio Kick Boxing, Filipino Martial Arts and Hatha Yoga.
Each of these disciplines are unique to all
foundations of the martial art styles. The mental benefits people have 
gained from this training are immeasurable.
We provide the edge that people need, now more than ever, to have confidence to rise in the toughest times.
Many of our staff have been teaching for over 25 years
and are professional, experienced, licensed instructors, who have 
dedicated their lives to sharing the power of martial arts with the 
community. We keep quality control with in the schools
and provide the perfect backdrop for developing the skill and 
determination needed to succeed in martial arts and other elements in Life.

The goal of the teachers at Scott Halsey's Kenpo Karate

times of need.  Martial arts allow people to be confident without the 
need to bully or belittle others.  Ultimately, the karate student is a 
strong and capable person who is a help to those around them in many 
ways.

are trained to identify and handle problem situations. Martial Arts can
be whatever you want it to be and Kuntau is your guide. At work, school
or in your home you have problems that appear and try to disrupt your 
life. Kuntau is not about fighting its about solving problems.
If you take your own destiny in hand, then you'll be the most successful 
person on this earth. Every person has a purpose or a destiny you must

go out and get it yourself. If its not important then send someone else

 hand and weapon based combat disciplines using Okinawan Shorin Ryu 
Karate as the base art. The incorporation of the empty hand art of 
Awaten Combat Ju Jutsu, Tae Kyon (Tae Kwon Do), Yang Luchuan Tai Chi, Gee Joh Acupressure and Dimmak, the weapon based arts of Filipino Stick and Knife Fighting, Japanese Sword Art of Goshindo, and Okinawan Kudodu Weaponry, define the Sungadan system.

The Brea Shaolin Kung Fu School is celebrated its 29th year
 of business in Brea, California on August 3rd, 2014!  For many years, 
we have taught men, women and children three major styles of Traditional
 Chinese Martial Arts – Northern Shaolin Long Fist, Praying Mantis, and 
Tai Chi.  Each style is extremely famous and offers the prospective 
student physical and mental fitness by increasing strength, confidence, 
and self-control.  These are the key ingredients for a person’s 
self-defense abilities.  Not only will you learn the physical principles
 of self-defense, but also begin to gain the awareness you need to 
recognize and avoid problems.

Monterey Budokan is a martial arts academy located in Monterey, CA.We 
offer several martial arts for unification of mind, body and 
spirit.Martial Arts for Adults, Juniors and Children.

column1: Los Angeles Traditional Wing Chun Kung Fu Academy
column8:
Wing Chun Kung Fu is a very aggressive Southern Chinese style of martial arts. It is comprised of compact movements, and characterized by rapid straight-lineattacks that leave adversaries defenseless. Designed by China's Shaolin Temple Grandmasters using only the most efficient techniques of all 
known Kung Fu styles, Wing Chun develops students to proficiency in 5 to
7 years. Most other systems require 15 to 20 years to master. Wing Chun
is simple and easy to learn. Combine discipline with our traditional 
training methods and improve your fitness, confidence, and self-defense.
Wing Chun Kung Fu is suitable for all individuals.

The Shotokan Karate Institute is a traditional Karate dojo recognized by the Japan Karate Association and the American Amateur Karate Federation. The Shotokan Karate Institute is located in Northern 
California, on the eastern shore of the San Francisco Bay. It is 
conveniently located at the El Cerrito/Richmond border, right off of 
Interstate 80. Students train here from all over the Bay Area including 
Oakland, Berkeley, San Francisco, Davis, Santa Clara, Concord and Daly 
City. Visitors are welcome to observe any class.

Taught by 9th degree blackbelt and founder grandmaster Tom Gwak, Hap Do Sool is a unique and original Korean martial art comprised of several different martial arts styles and health systems. These techniques and influences stem from a variety of disciplines such as tae kwon do, boxing, jujitsu, judo, aikido, gymnastics and yoga. Focusing on mental, physical, and spiritual development and awareness, Hap Do Sool also teaches traditional values of respect, courtesy, honesty, diligence, humility, responsibility, and obedience.

Salim's Taekwondo Center has been a positive influence in the community 
for more than 9 years. With our dedicated staff and instructors you can 
be sure that your child is receiving the best training possible.

Model Mugging Self-Defense provides students the greatest impact in 
personal safety and overcoming personal fears of being assaulted through
role model mastery. Many self-defense courses are simply comprised of a
group of techniques without continuity between techniques, strategy, 
and the reality of effectiveness for women.
Rape defense eye strike applied full force during Model Mugging self-defense course.
Other programs have copied our innovative teaching methods and padded assailant concept. There are many choices in self-defense
and personal safety measures. Briefly, the Model Mugging curriculum is 
founded on researching thousands crimes, review of academic literature, 
martial arts, and decades of experience conducting reality based 
self-defense scenarios.
It is important that you assess your goals for personal protection when considering your options in personal protection and self-defense training.

American Martial Arts Academy was founded in 1992 by 
Shihan Brad Wenneberg. We were founded on the principles of teaching 
excellence, personal attention, and tradition. Since 1994, we have been 
ranked as one of the top martial arts schools in the entire nation. We 
help our students develop physically and mentally. 
Our mission is: To provide the finest instruction in the mental, physical, and character building aspects of the martial arts.To provide personal instruction in every class.To provide the best professional facilities in the area.To create an environment that gives each individual the opportunity 
to pursue and achieve a greater level of personal success and freedom.

Our school offers a well-rounded Traditional Martial Arts program concentrating on Shorinji-Ryu, a style of Okinawan Karate. Character development is placed at the forefront of our teachings with 
the underlying theme of Respect. We teach that, "Karate Begins and ends 
with Respect." Our staff of certified professional instructors are 
devoted to helping students increase their fitness, stamina and 
strength, as they achieve a new level of mind and body coordination and 
confidence. Our excellent self-defense training integrates the kicking, 
punching, striking and blocking skills of Karate, along with the joint 
locks, arm bars, submission holds and movements of Aikijujutsu. We also 
offer a Tai Chi program.

At the KSW Karate Dojo we want to offer the very best training 
experience possible at the most affordable price possible.  We are 
always looking for new ways to improve your training experience and for 
classes that will make a healthful, active lifestyle more accessible to 
everyone in a way that compliments their personal preferences.

The focus of U. S. Tae Kwon Do Center West Covina is to guide the student in the educational martial arts training, 
Tae Kwon Do. Because it promotes a healthy body and disciplined mind, and helps them build their character to become a leader who strives for the excellence.

The Eagle Claw Kung Fu Academy of Sacramento was founded in 1988 by Master Benson Lee, under the name Ying Jow Pai Kung Fu Academy. Master Lee began his training as a student of Grandmaster Shum Leung in
New York City in 1976. In 2005, After teaching classes under Master Lee
and administering the school for 10 years, Sifu Mark Purkeypile became 
the primary instructor of the school. Sifu Purkeypile currently resides 
in Fredericksburg, Virginia, where he continues to practice and teach 
Ying Jow Pai and Wu tai chi chuan privately.Currently, Sifu Mary 
Melliza, also a student of Master Benson Lee, teaches classes and 
administers the day-to-day aspects of the School. Master Benson Lee 
resides in Glendale, California, where he continues to teach Ying Jow 
Pai and Wu tai chi chuan.

EMAC Taekwondo program is an exciting martial arts 
program focusing on character development, physical fitness and 
practical self-defense. 
Through fun, cooperative workouts, we strive to 
provide students with the skills, energy and confidence to pursue their 
dreams and to make a useful contribution to the world.

Established in Antioch, CA in 1988.  Moved to Brentwood, CA in 2002.  
Styles include Isshinryu karate, Alemany kenpo, Modern Arnis, Doce Pares
Eskrima, Muay Thai, Kemscrima-Doh, Gracie Jiu-Jitsu.

Founded in 1975 on the principles of teaching excellence, personal 
attention and tradition, for more than 40 years, Robinson’s Taekwondo 
provides you with the most complete and effective methods to reach your 
full potential.While self-defense techniques are often the first thought in choosing
Taekwondo as a martial art, most students quickly discover the healthy fitness, positive attitudes and mental sharpness that come from physical training. Both adults and children benefit by controlling weight, 
increasing strength, endurance and flexibility while gaining confidence 
from achieving greater respect for themselves and others. Robinson’s Taekwondo has taught thousands of students in the past 40 years, including many USAT, US Open and UWTA champion athletes. 
Robinson’s students from Elk Grove won the Gold and Silver Medals at the 2010 U.S. Open in Austin, TX.

Our martial arts academies offer great martial arts training.  When you commit to 
train at any of our licensed facilities, you can be assured that you are learning
from professional instructors and leaders in your community. Our Masters and 
Instructors are world certified, constantly attend seminars  and are re-certified bi-annually
by Grandmasters which are all internationally certified.referee, as well as by other world renowned Grandmasters. 
Our martial arts facilities are unique, family-oriented training centers, dedicated to teaching proper self defense and furthering the mental and physical inner  strength of each individual. Our commitment is to help all individuals become the best they can be. Our specialized martial arts programs for ages 3 years to adult are designed to develop character, self discipline, self defense, success, goal setting, leadership and life skills. We do not teach violence, but we do teach a more intense program of self-defense. Our students also improve in self discipline, self control, self determination, perseverance, concentration, cooperation, 
confidence, respect, integrity and learning to deal with life’s daily stress and any negativity that can muddle up our lives.

Ken Carr's Martial Arts Schools teach traditional Okinawan style karate and kobudo. We teach the orthodox Kobayash-Ryui (Shorin-Ryu) that was handed down from the original masters of modern karate.  
We accept students of all ages and ability; from novice to advanced martial artists. We also have our Samurai Kids program specially designed for pre-school and kindergarten age children.We also have one of the only comprehensive master level Kobudo (weapons) programs in Southern California. Kyoju Ken Carr teaches traditional 
Japanese/Okinawan weapons from staff to sword.

At our schools of Chinese martial arts-Hei Long Shou Shu Kung Fu, our students young and old embrace a way of life full of confidence, self-discipline, and self-control that will enhance mind, body and spirit. Hei Long Shou Shu Kung Fu (Black Dragon Beast Art) is a combative art that incorporates the fighting principles of seven different animals. Our schools provide classes for men, women, and especially children in a family oriented atmosphere.We are the only schools in the U.S. that teach Hei Long Shou Shu Kung Fu.
Through high quality martial arts instruction we empower people of all ages to achieve their full potential.

column1: Golden Dragon Chinese Kung Fu and Culture Institute
column8:
At Golden Dragon we teach our students confidence, discipline, and 
self-motivation. We accomplish this through our afterschool program led 
by our experienced teaching faculty. We also provide Kung Fu / Wushu 
classes taught first hand by renowned Grand Master Ma JinLong and his 
professional coaching staffs. We guarantee a safe and engaging 
experience for students of all ages.

Using traditional values and modern techniques through Martial Arts, we forge a self development and Character formation.This program promotes a healthy mind, self-confidence, self-discipline and high self-esteem, as well as encourages the pursuit of excellence.

Kuntau is a way to protect yourself in real life. Kuntau teaches you how to use your natural weapons and use an attackers power and strengths against themselves. You are trained to identify and handle problem situations. Martial Arts can be whatever you want it to be and Kuntau is your guide. At work, school or in your home you have problems that appear and try to disrupt your life. Kuntau is not about fighting its about solving problems.
If you take your own destiny in hand, then you'll be the most successful person on this earth. Every person has a purpose or a destiny you must seek yours so you can fulfill it. When you want something. You have to 
go out and get it yourself. If its not important then send someone else or wait for it to come to you.

Judo America San Diego is a non-profit organization dedicated to the 
development of the individual.  Through the discipline of Judo, we build
character and promote physical fitness and positive social values.  We 
provide a safe environment for students to channel their natural 
aggression into self-control and teamwork, and we encourage the 
development of personal excellence.

We teach Japanese Jujutsu, Batto-Do (Japanese Swordsmanship), Women's Self Defense, as well as Japanese Language Skills (from beginner to advanced). In addition, we offer private lessons and also a well developed children's program. 
Our Jujutsu specializes in wrist and joint locks, throws/takedowns, holds, and pins by utilizing bone structure, natural movement, and painful pressure points.
The origin of this art dates back to feudal Japan, where the techniques were studied by the Samurai.

East West MMA offers a variety of martial arts experiences, ranging from children's martial arts training and combat fitness to get you into shape all the way to MMA and Brazilian Jiu Jitsu You'll be impressed with our fantastic staff! Everybody here at East West MMA Escondido has been professionally trained to teach you everything you'll need to be successful here. They are all professional martial artists that are passionate about helping you to achieve your goals. You'll be comfortable knowing that everythingyou're taught is being taught safely and properly so that you can learn quickly, get into great shape and avoid injuries.

Kukkido Martial Arts offers a comprehensive martial arts training system that teaches different techniques fromTaekwondo, Aikido, Cardio Kick Boxing, Filipino Martial Arts and Hatha Yoga.Each of these disciplines are unique to all foundations of the martial art styles. The mental benefits people have 
gained from this training are immeasurable. We provide the edge that people need, now more than ever, to have confidence to rise in the toughest times. Many of our staff have been teaching for over 25 years
and are professional, experienced, licensed instructors, who have dedicated their lives to sharing the power of martial arts with the community.We keep quality control with in the schools and provide the perfect backdrop for developing the skill and determination needed to succeed in martial arts and other elements in Life.
CKA offers Self Defense based martial arts training in Karate, full contact Kickboxing, Grappling & Traditional Weapons for All Ages

Since first opening in 2003 Champion Eyes has been steadfast in its dedication to traditional martial arts, self defense and weaponry. The skills learned through training are used to streangthen our students both in and outside of the dojo. Having many national and international tournament Champions our instructors exemplify the power of achieving goals. Whether in their martial arts training, personal, schoolastic, or proffessional lives, the skills learned are vital in 
setting and realizing their goals.
Our students utilize their skills to acheive personal goals, Whether at home, school or professionally, our students obtains their goals through putting into practice the basics.Dedication, commitment, and focus, these elements adhered to daily are the corner stones to realizing their goals. Echa goal attained whether small or large, 
streangthens their confidence and provides the encouragement for even greater aspirations.

We offer the following types of martial arts: MMA / KICKBOXING, BRAZILIAN JIU-JITSU & FITNESS CLASSES
  •   MMA / Kickboxing - Always starts with respect and ends with respect.  Training generally is divided into the practice of techniques and sparring.  We supplement these punches and kicks with self-defense techniques and overall endurance and flexibility training.
   •   Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu training takes place in a formal atmosphere with an emphasis on etiquette and self-control as well as physical ability.  While grappling, students stop by tapout just short of injury so that power is always maintained with control. Gi and no Gi classes are available.
  •   Fitness classes for adults and kids include functional exercises for fitness and combat sports. All through the world you will see that wild animals are in far better shape than human
At Quest, our goal is to develop strong minds, body and spirit through the practice of Taekwondo. Our Quest is to build a better community, one Black Belt at a time.

SK Tae Kwon Do Studio is dedicated to the highest quality of martial 
arts training. We are committed to continually enhancing our program to address exercise, drills, safety tips and a realistic approach to self-defense situations. We "Build Confidence Through Achievement" and 
provide an environment conducive to positive relationships, fostering self-discipline and self-confidence and self-respect.

Here at Ultimate Taekwondo the focus is on YOU - your personal goals for fitness, self esteem, and your chance to be a part of something that will change your life forever. Martial Arts are the best way for reducing stress and getting fit very quickly. After a few classes, you will notice improvements in flexibility, athletic stamina, and self confidence all while lowering body fat and those unwanted inches.

The Shaolin Wushu Center offers a variety of classes in Gongfu (Kung Fu) and Taiji (T'ai Chi) for athletes of all ages and athletic abilities--from the novice to the seasoned international competitor. Training is available in many styles of open-hand and weapons traditions, including northern and southern fist, staff, broadsword, 
straight sword, 9-section chain-whip, mimetic animal styles such as praying mantis, snake and eagle, and various styles of taiji and qigong.Classes are also available in stage combat and choreography. Group training and private lessons are available.The Shaolin Wushu Center also has an international exchange program that gives our students the opportunity to visit and train in China.

Today, Sweet Pete's Martial Arts Academy is renowned for it's innovative teaching methods, 
scenario-based self-defense work and highly effective sparring drills. 
Pete's approach to   instructing is considered very unique, as is his 
close relationship with his students, instructors, parents and other 
martial artists. At Sweet Pete's Martial Arts Academy people say you can
 sense the camaraderie and the Lord's presence.

The Teachers at Sifu Meng£r Kung Fu Academy teach a step by step process. The training program is broken down to give the students a solid foundation of basics, and gradually increases the skills to 
more advanced, and even professional levels of training. The basics include, strong stances, and proper kicking 
and punching technique. The advanced includes, application of techniques, and highly coordinated kicking, 
punching, and flipping movements. Along the journey the students make from beginner to advanced, an adequate 
foundation of flexibility, strength, coordination, and discipline will be instilled into each individual. 
Each student goes at their own pace, and the teachers match the students learning style to insure that they succeed.

column1: Kuk Sool Won of San Lorenzo
column8:
Kuk Sool Won, which can be translated to Korean National Martial art 
association, is a systematic study of all the traditional fighting arts which together comprise the martial art history of the Korean nation.  As such, Kuk Sool Won is an extremely well-organized system of martial arts which seeks to integrate and explore all aspects of the traditional Korean Martial arts.  As a martial arts 
system, Kuk Sool Won covers the entire spectrum of the traditional Asian fighting arts
 and techniqes of body conditioning as well as mental development and 
traditional weapon training.

We are specialized in Beginners, Kids Bullyproof and Self-Defense. Our 
Programs are designed by Saulo and Xande Ribeiro, the most decorated 
family in the sport. San Diego’s Best BJJ School, affiliated to Ribeiro Jiu-Jitsu Association, we are your choice for traditional martial arts in a fun, safe and clean environment. Oss!

Stockton Kuk Sool is a traditional Korean martial art and has been established for 18+ years. Stockton Kuk Sool has instructed hundreds of people throughout San Joaquin area and has received recognition in San Joaquin Magazine and received countless awards from the community. Stockton Kuk Sool's instructors are very experienced and have a set goal to help each student grow physically and mentally in order to develop great martial artist and a better community. Stockton Kuk Sool is a complete martial art that covers a wide range of punching,kicking, throwing, tumbling, techniques, sparring and forms (both open hand and weapons).

WE ARE A RECOGNIZED SCHOOL OF BLACK BELT EXCELLENCE Pallen Martial Arts, Castro 
Valley, CA, is one of the premier martial arts schools in all of Northern California. We are conveniently located just off of the 580 freeway (Marketplace Shopping Center) in the East Bay Area. Although our techniques are based on 
centuries-old knowledge, our application of that knowledge sets Pallen Martial Arts apart from other schools. We realize that each student possesses different physical abilities. Size and strength varies with each individual, so once you have acquired a strong foundation in the basics, our program will enhance your own physical capabilities and maximize your self-defense skills. You'll understand exactly what it takes, mentally and physically, to defend yourself or your loved ones should the need ever arise.

Our academy was established to provide survival skills, through techniques of Tae 
Kwon Do and Hap ki Do. Our services include self-discipline, physical conditioning, and
self-defense.  We also offer a host of specialty services that cater to the unique needs of our students.

Our vision is to provide high quality and professional Martial Arts instruction.  The focus is on the individual developement of each student through a realistic and progressive training regimine.  We are a non-commercial school and as such we do not require additional associations, expensive clubs, extra fee's, or anything else that would detract from the further development of the student.  This benefit allows NCMA instructors to continually refine our technique and focus more time on students. Like many hometown companies we care about quality.  We care so much because ultimately our students presonal well being could be at stake.  For this reason we take a very realisitic approach to training; we use what works! Further our students are what make for a great environment to train in and as such we have a responsibility to ensure we meet their expectations.  At NCMA we are very fortunate to have students from all over join us every day! Thank you for taking the time to find out about our programs and we look forward to seeing you on the mats soon!

The UWTA is headed up by Grand Master Jong H. Lee, 9th Degree Black Belt and was founded in 1993. The UWTA has thrived ever since, due to the unique character building approach to Traditional Martial Arts Training.
The UWTA stresses the critical importance of mental and physical balance, essential to the true success in Traditional Arts of study. The UWTA assists students in leading healthier and happier lives, with an emphasis on concentration and self-confidence, needed for success in today's society. The philosophical approach of our traditional method of instruction, focuses on the balance of the student's physical and mental well being. This helps to instill the concept of courtesy, integrity, perseverance, self-control, indomitable spirt, and physical fitness, the essence of the UWTA spirit.

Schu-Fu is a sport-medicine based art with a scientific foundation. The focus is on self-defense, self improvement, stress relief and fitness.It is known as an eclectic style, which means that Schu-Fu includes the theory and technique of many styles of martial arts.  You do not need athletic ability, strength, or size to learn Schu-Fu, because the art teaches you how to use your opponent's energy against them.Grand Master Schu and his dedicated staff understand that people have different needs and abilities.  Thus, everyone who attends class is treated as an individual and encouraged to advance at their own pace.At Schu-Fu, we strive to help people develop their warrior spirit with a curriculum that offers traditional methods of training mixed with simulations of real-world self defense situations.At Schu-Fu, our motto is, " You do what you practice ".  Therefore, we engage in full-contact training with due emphasis on safety.  Schu-fu is not for tournament competition because tournament fight involves rules, and we all know that in the street, there are no rules.Schu-Fu International Martial Arts Association is dedicated to providing affordable, professional martial arts instruction for men, women and children of all ages.

The California Martial Arts Academy teaches traditional Kung Fu for students of all ages.  Classes are structured so that students can grow and enjoy their training at their own level, all while having fun in a group atmosphere.
The goal for all our programs is to create a community where our students can flourish and enjoy the challenging journey that is traditional kung fu.Please visit our Programs page to learn more about what we have to offer.

Sabum Nim Shawn J. Stallworth, the creator and pioneer of Panther Energy Tae Kwon Do, has dedicated his life to the study of martial arts. Blessed with a gift for martial arts at an early age, he advanced quickly in the art forms. He has dedicated the better part of his adult life to sharing his gift with others, as a Head Instructor and Personal Trainer.

Our goal is to uphold the true spirit of Shotokan Karate, develop the 
character, mentor and empower the student and improve quality of life.

At Tenshin-Kai Taichi and Karate, people of all ages from all over the world gather to improve themselves, to 
learn and grow through the arts of taichi and karate, under the instruction of Grand Master Tenzan Hirakawa.

column1: California Kung Fu and Tai Chi Institute
column8: We try our best to promote both the physical and spiritual growth in our students by teaching both the external and internal martial arts styles. Our ultimate goal is to enhance a student's life through the understanding and application of the values and discipline taught in the Chinese Martial Art styles, traditions and culture.

Our mission is to strive for excellence while providing quality instruction to each and every karate-ka (student) who entrusts his or her Body, Mind and Spirit to our dojo. We are committed to the education of all of our karate-kas as well as providing for the dojo's needs in the most empathetic and professional environment possible. Our intent is
that the benefits of our commitment to excellence will positively impact the lives of our instructors, karate-kas and the community we serve.

In 1986, Lama's Kenpo Karate began  as an idea to facilitate the art of Shaolin Kenpo to friends and family members in the Bernal Heights community as a way to build  self-confidence, awareness,  and self-defense. In the mid 80's, the  Bernal Heights neighborhood was known to have an above average crime  rate, which included random assaults, robberies, and the selling of  illegal drugs. It made walking the streets unsafe during any time of the day. Although, this was considered a rough neighborhood it was Professor  Lama's vision to share his knowledge in self-defense  so that others may benefit.Professor Lama first began teaching out of his  own garage where he only had five students.  The space was very limited, but Professor managed to teach katas and conduct sparring sessions in his 12'x18' garage space. His motivation and  combined passion for teaching encouraged him to open up his first formal  karate studio in Bernal Heights. After  four successful years in  business, Lama's Kenpo Karate expanded and moved into a larger location  in Bernal Heights. As enrollment increased at Lama's Kenpo Karate, Sibok Lama moved the school to its present day location in San Bruno, Ca. It is here that Professor continues  to build self-confidence, awareness, and discipline into his students.

Beverly Hills Jiu-Jitsu Club offers a variety of classes for all levels.We provide training for competition, tournaments, self defense or if you just want a fun and challenging workout to be in top shape.

Whether you’re new to martial arts or have been training for years, White Dragon has the program that is right for you. Our unique combination of Kung Fu, Tai Chi, Kickboxing & Grappling - MMA creates a complete, well rounded training experience: Kung Fu for practical self defense, Tai Chi to relieve stress and improve health, Kickboxing & Grappling - MMA for fun, high intensity workouts that build strength and cardiovascular fitness.Established in 1985, White Dragon is one of Southern California’s oldest & largest martial arts schools. We stand apart from other schools because one on one private lessons are included in every membership. This means that you’ll safely and effectively achieve your goals while working with some of the most dedicated instructors anywhere.At White Dragon Martial Arts 
we guarantee to transform your life by teaching you the most complete and effective system of martial arts and health improvement available today. We promise to serve you at the highest standards of ethics and excellence in teaching, so that you can go beyond your limitations, reach your fullest potential, and achieve your most important life goals.

We are an independent family owned and professional full service martial arts academy located in Santa Rosa.  We offer exciting classes 6 days a week taught by certified black belt instructors.  We have been serving Sonoma County since 1993.  Our curriculum is age specific and relevant for every age group.

We pride ourselves on being what we call a "family school". This is a term that we always use to describe our school and our program. It simply means that we welcome all people, from every aspect of our community, to come together in our school to learn the martial arts. Our program provides for a diverse collection of people that includes both men, women, and children of all ages. Our students are kids, mothers, fathers, college students, business owners, teachers,
and professionals. Our students come from all over Davis and the surrounding areas. Their ages range from 5 to 50 and all work together toward the success of all. For many, achieving the rank of Black Belt is the goal of a lifetime. So often, our older students will tell you that this was something they always wanted to do but could never find quite the right environment to do it in. But, they found the right formula here in our school. The parents of our younger students 
will tell you of the positive impact the karate program has had on their child and how the family environment of the school has contributed to this. Parents and children are encouraged to learn the martial arts side by side. Our school has a history of families participating and training together. Many families have gone through the program and earned their Black Belts together.

Founded in 1984, in the same location as it is today, Aikido of San Leandro has always had the same instructor and style of training. In our creative, challenging atmosphere, beginners are consistently taught with care and respect, with emphasis in clear, precise movements, which become graceful and effective techniques. The instructor, Pat Hendricks Sensei, holds a 7th degree black belt, and has trained exclusively in Iwama, Japan. Pat Sensei holds the highest degree possible in "Aiki Ken and Jo Certification," and is certified to hold examinations for the United States. Aikido of San Leandro attracts students from all over the world, including Japan, as well as from all over the Bay Area.

Located in the Greater Los Angeles area, TARZANA AIKIKAI is affiliated with the United States Aikido Federation (USAF), under the direction andsupport of Y. Yamada Shihan and Aikido Hombu Dojo,Tokyo, Japan. Chief Instructor Rob Hyatt, 4th dan, and  Instructor Nancy Supanich, 2nd dan, are students of Yamada Shihan and the late Kanai Shihan, both of whom are direct students of the founder of Aikido, O'Sensei Morihei Ueshiba. Tarzana Aikikai is affiliated with and supports the United States Aikido Federation, a 501 ©(3) nonprofit educational institution created for the purpose of spreading and maintaining the integrity of the Japanese martial art Aikido, a modern, nonviolent martial art also known as the "Art of Peace".

Welcome to our studios. We have prepared this brochure to introduce you to the Art of Karate-Do and Shito-Ryu Karate-Do Genbu-Kai of America. KARATE: a Japanese word meaning "empty" (Kara) and "hand" (The). It is asystem of attack and defense that used all parts of the body (hands, feet, elbows, fingers, etc.) to kick, punch, chop, but or any other move that is effective in defending yourself. Many of the movements have been analyzed and geometrically calculated so that wherever the action, a block or a punch, it is the maximum the human body can achieve. One quickly learns that it is not the size and strength alone that are the deciding factors in who will emerge victorious in physical combat.

column1: Association for Shotokan Karate of Napa
column8: The Association for Shotokan Karate of Napa (ASKN) is devoted to the teaching and promotion of the art of Karate.  We are part of an international organization, the largest Karate group in the world, the ISKF (International Shotokan Karate Federation).  This membership ensures the highest standard and uniformity of teaching, ranking and competition judging. ASKN was born in May 1985.   Founded by Sensei Greg Leonard, Yondan (4th degree Black Belt) and assisted by his wife, Candace Hammond, Nidan (2nd degree Black Belt), they offered classes to the public in various training spaces.  In early 1988, they opened their first dojo at 714 First St. in Napa. After many years of dedicated teaching and leadership, Sensei Leonard retired in May 2001.  Instruction continued under the guidance of his most senior student, Chela Morales-Placone, Godan (5th degree Black Belt).  She and her husband, Rick Placone, Yondan (4th degree Black Belt) carry on the tradition of Shotokan Karate in Napa adhering to the high standards and excellence in teaching established by their teacher, Sensei Leonard.

Kid Gloves is an organization dedicated to educating our students in the art of self defense as well as achieving physical excellence through proper nutrition and fitness. We will provide positive reinforcement by acknowledging our students progress both in physical and scholastic achievements. To achieve physical and scholastic excellence, our students will realize (at their own pace) that with dedication, self-discipline and hard work, these can be accomplished.

Established in 1996, Panther Martial Arts Center was formed because Master Urbistondo recognized the need for quality martial arts. In today's society, many martial arts schools teach strictly for the business side and therefore "water down" their martial arts. Panther Martial Arts Center's number one priority is quality martial arts instruction. We like to build confidence and teach effective self-defense training that works. Our motto at Panther is "Above & Beyond."  We help our students apply that motto to all aspects of their lives including self-defense, job deadlines, weight loss, homework assignments and more. Panther Martial Arts Center offers something for everyone in the family.

Foothill Taekwondo is owned and operated by Mr. Bob Westphal and Mrs. Connie Westphal, 6th degree black belts both ITC National Sparring Champions and Certified instructors. We at Foothill Taekwondo are dedicated to giving you the most professional, well supervised and highest quality classes available in any sport anywhere! We offer training in Tae Kwon Do, beginner through black belt for all ages and weapons training.

Koei-Kan Karate-Do of San Luis Obispo is dedicated to providing the best in martial arts instruction. Martial arts, as exemplified in Koei-Kan, are an essential means of developing physical skills of balance and coordination, good conditioning, effective self-defense, personal poise and self-confidence, even strength of character. Kids and Juniors classes are held in the afternoon; adult classes in the evening. Visitors and drop-ins are welcome. Two free lessons are offered. Rates available on request.

Providing a proactive, friendly environment for our members to achieve their personal goals in martial arts and physical fitness. We seek to enhance the quality of life in our community through our diverse and affordable fitness philosophy.

Since 1982, CAL-WEST KARATE SCHOOL has been a leader in Martial Arts training in the Bay Area. In that time we have taught thousands of students, of all ages, the Art of Self-Defense.Our spacious 2,800 square foot facility is uniquely designed with padded mats, private lesson rooms, and special workout areas. Our highly trained professional staff can help each student achieve their maximum proficiency at all levels. We strive to teach all students to compete against themselves and to be the best they can be. Self-esteem, self-confidence, self-discipline, and respect for others are the keys to our program and to success in school, work, sports, and family life. Our "Personal Trainer Program" provides one-on -one attention, ensuring proper guidance and instruction to each student. Positive, patient, and effective teaching techniques will enable them to learn more and learn faster. Special attention is given to children to make learning easier, fun, and rewarding.With all the violence and chaos in the world today, it is our desire to help all our students to walk the streets safely, overcome their obstacles, obtain their goals, and lead a rich and fulfilling life.

Jobu Shin Kan is a traditional martial arts school dedicated to development of character through the study of Danzan Ryu Jujitsu. Our purpose is to provide a healthy and safe atmosphere to support the physical and mental growth of our students in their all-around pursuit of excellence. We welcome students of all ages, sizes, and body types.

America's Best Chatsworth Karate has been offering instruction and training in Tang Soo Do since 1990. Located in Chatsworth, CA, America's
Best Chatsworth Karate has produced champions in life as well as in the martial arts. Headed by Mark Cox (6th Degree Black Belt) and a staff of expert instructors and managers,  including Nathan 
Carlen, Kenny Broderick,Chris Pulos, and Matt Nadel. America's Best Chatsworth Karate offers a number of programs for physical fitness and instruction in  Tang Soo Do.
