As a leading provider of Martial Arts instruction, we take pride in offering the best quality self defense instruction. We are dedicated to serving the needs of our customers each and every day. We only use Black Belt instructors that are qualified in all styles of martial arts. We are a modern American Mixed Martial Arts System that is taught as a reality-based self-defense. Using anything that works and having no limitations in our style. We have always and will continue to teach "LEARN AND USE WHAT WORKS FOR YOU."

column1: The Little Gym of Mountain View
column8: The Little Gym helps children build the confidence and skills needed at each stage of childhood.  Each week, structured classes and our unique learning environment will create opportunities for your child to try new things and build self-confidence.  As your child grows and develops new physical skills, you will see a noticeable positive difference with each new achievement, but your child will simply see The Little Gym as a place to have fun, laugh, and make new friends.  That's just fine by us.  Who said learning had to be so serious?  Why not let them have some Serious Fun! We have classes from 4 months all the way up to 12 years.  Call us to schedule a FREE Introductory Visit!

Foothill Shotokan is a nonprofit organization lead by Marty Cullenward,who first began training in 1973. Marty has obtained the level of godan, or fifth degree black belt, the highest ranking possible within SKA.Foothill Karate-do was founded in 1987 by Bob Root and Dave Rose. They began training with SKA in 1980. Bob and Dave are third degree black belt instructors (sandan). Dave is retired from the Placer County Sheriff’s Department and continues to teach defense courses for law enforcement agencies. The dojo offers courses for regional residents of any age, at any stage of life. Students benefit through self-improvement and physical development. Self-esteem, flexibility, conditioning, martial skills — all of these tangible benefits are achieved through focus and dedication.  All sessions are lead by instructors with decades of experience.Foothill Karate-do and SKA offer the ingredients of successful martial arts training: One part physical mixed with one part mental and simmered with patience.

Master Mun founded ATC with the vision of providing school-aged children and adults of all ages a firm foundation in the mental, physical and ethical standards of Taekwondo. His goal is to create not only superior athletes, but responsible adults who live according to the tenets of courtesy, integrity, perseverance and self-control. While his rank and experience would qualify him to make a career of coaching already accomplished university athletes, Grand Master Mun has instead dedicated himself to a program of high-quality education for people of all ages. Grand Master Mun is a living example of all that embodies Taekwondo; knowledgeable, patient, respectable and a person of integrity in and outside of the dojang. His belief in what he does and in his students allows him to help them reach their highest potential. He truly cares about all his students and assists them anyway possible. Master Mun helps his students in setting and reaching their goals in Taekwondo as well as in their personal lives. Grand Master Mun also likes to volunteer his time and efforts into worthy causes for children and donates to his community.

When we say we’re a life-enhancement facility as much as we are a gym, it isn’t some sort of gimmick. Despite its undeserved violent reputation, Mixed Martial Arts can be a powerful ool in effecting positive change. Students not only lose weight, get in shape, and learn potentially life-saving skills, they build confidence, develop a strong body and mind, and develop mindset traits that serve them well in all areas of life. Maybe that’s why it’s not just the fastest-growing sport in America (according to Sports Illustrated), workout gurus such as Jillian Michaels from “The Biggest Loser” listed it in Time Magazine as the one workout she’d choose if she could pick only one workout regimen. All this doesn’t mean we’re running fad exercise programs. Classes at M3 Fight and Fitness are geared toward the individual. We will be there every step of the way with you on your journey with friendly, supportive instructors and fellow students who are encouraged to follow suit. Whether your mission is to be a champion or just improve yourself, we are all one team working together to reach your goal!
A mixed martial arts gym offering classes in boxing, muay thai kickboxing, Brazilian jiu-jitsu, judo and submission wrestling.

John Barrett American Martial Arts is a very progressive and natural self-defense oriented school. The system is based on fluid and natural movements using body, hands and feet. The aim is to develop talents which are easily applied in real life situations. The style is best described as a hybrid system of the most effective martial arts incorporated into one.

Established in 1993, Boxing Works began delivering something that was lacking in the South Bay area, a facility devoted to teaching the art of western Boxing.  Roughly the same time the gym was opened, the Ultimate Fighting Championship debuted on Pay Per View.  Seeing the imbalance of only offering one approach to training, Boxing Works began incorporating other systems into their curriculum, including Jiu-jitsu and Muay Thai, while keeping their roots in Western Boxing. We specialize in Muay Thai, Boxing, and MMA for everyone from the casual enthusiast to the professional fighter.  Men, Women, Children are all welcome!

Welcome to Antelope Valley’s best, most complete, and fastest growing martial arts and fitness training facility offering Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu, Judo, Fitness Kickboxing, Mixed Martial Arts, Boxing, Muay-Thai, No-Gi, Strength & Conditioning, Boot Camp, Kettlebells, Interval Training, and Self-Defense classes for kids and adults!

With building confidence, we offer extra incentives to your child and our young students with patches, along side of belts and stripes, to acknowledge their growth through the ranks and among their new friends they will meet. As the instructors and parents will testify, they have seen many of our young students improve in self-esteem, flexibility, hand eye coordination, calm behavior after class, heightened listening skills, and most importantly, that our young Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu martial artists are having fun!

At Carlson Gracie Temecula we are constantly training. Everyone has a different schedule so we have morning classes, evening classes, private instruction and LOTS open mat.  Saturdays and Sundays are not exempt. Please see our schedule for details. Students range from 3 years old to active practitioners in their 60’s. The majority of our students experience a lot of personal self discoverythrough improved fitness and stress relief. This extends to family and friends, who often come and join to experience the same benefits! The single most inspiring aspect we encounter is witnessing the transformation our students go through as they learn to overcome personal obstacles and combat fear, depression, anxiety and become empowered with a humble sense of confidence while getting in shape in the process.

SHORIN-RYU KARATE IS A TRADITIONAL OKINAWAN MARTIAL ART, AND A COMPLETE SELF-DEFENSE SYSTEM. IT USES BLOCKS, PUNCHES, KICKS, GRABS, LOCKS AND THROWS. TRAINING DEVELOPS DISCIPLINE, COORDINATION, TIMING, SPEED, BALANCE, PHYSICAL FITNESS, AND SELF-CONFIDENCE.

USAFMA has specialized in children's martial arts since 1986 and has one of the most progressive, innovative martial arts programs in the nation. We encourage education and 100% of our Junior Black Belt graduates are attending or are graduates of a university. On a competitive level we have three NASKA World martial art champions and a nationally rated performance team!  We pride ourselves on delivering a professional, nurturing family environment with caring Black Belt instructors. Our Black Belt instructors are internationally and nationally certified,have CPR and first aid training, and have a minimum of 10 years experience with USAFMA. We teach our own unique system of Freestyle Martial Arts (FMA) which incorporates: practical streetwise self defense skills (reacting under pressure), extreme martial arts (acrobatic sport performance), traditional martial arts (karate / tae kwon do / judo), and mixed martial arts (sport grappling and kickboxing). Through our unique system of FMA, we emphasize the importance of "Character Development" such as confidence, discipline, respect, focus, and perseverance.

Aikido Doshinokai provides a safe, convenient, and welcoming environment for all practitioners. The open mat space is approximately 1200 square feet with additional space for male/female changing rooms, restroom, and observation seating area.  Building on the communal spirit of Aikido, students have full access to the dojo and participate in improvement and cleaning efforts together. Each class involves focused training based in the methodology of traditional Japanese martial arts.  Specifically, classes include warm-up and stretching exercises, demonstrations, and partnered practice.  Students of all levels train together and at their own paces.  This structure allows beginners to improve their skills quickly by working hand-in-hand with senior students and instructors.  Aikido training develops self-defense skills, physical fitness and spiritual awareness.Interested visitors are welcome to observe a class anytime; or attend a trial class for free.  Aikido practitioners visiting from out of town are welcome to attend classes appropriate for their skill level for a nominal mat fee.

Classes are led by qualified instructors in an ideal environment. Ourdedicated instructors will guide and train each student according to their aptitude for optimal result so that they can benefit from the three essential advantages of wushu – health, rejuvenation, and self-defense.

Cuong Nhu Redwood Dojo has offered traditional martial arts training to the Oakland community since 1992. With classes at the Redwood Heights Community Center, we provide serious, ongoing training in a beautiful facility, at a very low cost. Join us! Challenge yourself with a fun, rigorous workout that’s never boring. Build health, fitness and confidence. Learn skills for self defense.Sharpen your focus and concentration.Channel stress and aggression into a beautiful form of art.

At Victory our philosophy is to teach life skills.  Our Goal is to shape successful human beings - true champions - who will create a better world.  Therefore, we will focus on the skills of self-control including personal focus and on confidence - always doing your best.  Additionally, we reinforce respect in the classroom and at home; respect for our teachers, parents, and for others - all in a fun engaging environment.  Our programs are specifically designed to teach students to become successful leaders. We are committed to providing a safe, caring educational environment, supporting and actively encouraging the personal growth of our students. In our students who are children, we actively promote excellent behavior both at home and at school. We develop an awareness of the importance of fitness, health and hygiene, enhancing responsibility among our students. We are committed to empowering our students, for them to be successful in life.

Riverside Submission was established in 2004. We are now known as Riverside Submission/Arrey Jiu-Jitsu,highlighting 
Richard Arrey, the owner/Master Instructor and our specialty. We are also an Aloisio Silva Jiu-Jitsu affiliate school, in the tradition and honor of Aloisio Silva and the core principals of Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu. These core principles that continue to guide us are: Dedication, Perseverance, Respect, Loyalty, Discipline, and Honor.

Watch as your child increases in confidence, energy and spirit. Stand and be dazzled as he becomes unstoppable in his quest for... Greater academic achievement. Unshakable self respect. Increased strength and fitness, in both body and mind. And all of it comes while learning how to "kick, block, and punch." Look at it this way. Your child's first and biggest challenge comes not from "fighting for his rights on the street," or "beating up the neighborhood bully." It comes, instead, from battling more sinister forces. Your child's own fears and self doubts.

Adrenaline Combat Sports and Fitness is a full service fighting sports and traditional martial arts training center. Since we're located in San Bernardino near the 10 and 215 freeway we are within minutes of Colton,Highland,Bloomington, Rialto, Grand Terrace, Loma Linda, Redlands, Fontana and Riverside. We’re not just the largest training facility in the Inland Empire, with over 21,000 square feet of training area, 30 fitness and exercise machines, 25 boxing bags, and 4,000 square feet of mat area. We also have some if the best trainers in the Inland Empire and some of the best programs in place to take you and your family to the next level, whether it’s learning martial arts, getting and staying in shape, or competing at an amateur or professional level. Our trainers are also experienced in teaching small and large groups of students. We offer an extensive line of programs. For children 3 to adults who are interested in martial arts, self-defense, fighting sports, or just interested in getting in shape. Each program has an instructor at all times. Currently we offer Traditional Boxing, Brazilian Jiu Jitsu, Mixed Martial Arts, Muah Thai, Wrestling, Tang Soo Do, Judo, and Capoeira. We offer Gi and No Gi classes.For those interested in competing in fighting sports, we also hold amateur and professional events at our facility.

HMA Mission Statement We are defined as a Karate Assn. dedicated to the growth of all members. Our goal is to maintain a climate of enthusiasm, self-discovery and personal development; as well as social responsibility and contribution. Our Way of Life.

column1: Twin Tigers Academy of Self Defense
column8: Our academy's expertise is self-defense training for ages 4 and up. As part of the Hung Gar system, we teach students to have the opportunity to practice and learn movements with Martial arts weapons within a safe environment. Students will also have the opportunity to perform their weapon, self-defense forms, as well as sparring techniques in local tournaments. For those children and young adults, our martial arts program emphasizes many important values that help develop them into mentally strong and confident individuals. Besides the benefit of physical training, each child will be challenged with the help of our caring instructors to develop self confidence that will not only become prevalent in their martial arts training but also translate into their everyday lives.  Another important value taught at this academy is discipline. Students will learn the importance of respect, honor, leadership, and integrity through our teachings. Not only do we want your child to develop into a well trained martial artist but also to develop them into a well mannered and respectful individual.

column1: Power House MMA DMC Dynamic Movement Center
column8: Welcome to a whole new way to move. In being inspired by a new culture of movement we are redefining what it means to be athletic and physical, powerful and strong, flexible and balanced, agile and aware. We offer a home for a diverse collective of movement artists and specialists who are deeply immersed in their practices and enjoy sharing their well-seasoned experience. Learn from passionate, distinguished instructors who teach martial arts, dance, yoga, pilates, circus arts, strength and conditioning, and much more. Inspired by the belief that “when you move better your whole life is better” weʼve made it as easy as possible for people get out and play by offering special prices everyday for everyone. Come in when you want and for what you want with our member pass system. No monthly dues, or ball and chain contracts, or hidden cancellations fees. We invite you to embody your self with intention, with awareness and creativity, to bring strength and healing back into your body, to feel empowered and expressive in your movement and supported in leading a healthy and vibrant life.

Dedicated to helping change the world one black belt at a time! ATA Martial Arts is a member of one of the world's largest martial arts organizations, the American Taekwondo Association. Taekwondo is and exciting and powerful martial art known for its dynamic kicking and hand techniques. Although these martial arts techniques are centuries old, our programs are always evolving to keep pace with our rapidly changing world. The teaching curriculum at ATA Martial Arts is based on two concepts: "positive mental attitude" and "setting high goals". We feel so positive about our program that we promise to give you and your family the most professional, well supervised and highest quality classes available.

Welcome to the Poway Kenpo Karate School for kids, moms, dads, working professionals and athletes, helping you stay fit, active and healthy. Kenpo Karate is based upon the best overall aspects of Asian Martial Systems. What is Kenpo Karate? Kenpo Karate is a complete self defense fighting system of martial arts that teaches blocking and counterstrikes to vital organs and pressure points with linear and circular strikes and intermittent burst of speed and power. Some forms of martial arts specialize in a primary area of training – for example Tae Kwon do specializes in foot techniques, Judo on Body leveraging. Kenpo places equal emphasis on the use of hands, feet and body leveraging to overwhelm an opponent.

One of the first things you notice when entering a Joslin’s Martial Arts Center is the high energy levels.  There is plenty of fast action and broad smiles as our professional instructors lead students through the day’s curriculum. We are fortunate to have so many wonderful people and families training together at our school. Joslin’s is a safe family oriented school with a focus on one’s self improvement.While watching class you will be able to see and understand how we are able to instill positive life skills in addition to top notch martial arts instruction. Joslin’s martial arts programs are no secret. Master Ron Joslin have been working with parents, teachers and principals, developing their Dojo (school), since November 5th1977. When Master Ron Joslin was asked about all his achievements and awards he said, “The most rewarding part of what we do is seeing the positive changes in people’s lives”.

Here we teach traditional Okinawan karate-do and kobudo(weapons). We train in the Shorin Ryu Shorinkan style of Okinawan karate under the leadership of Hanshi (10th degree blackbelt) Shuguro Nakazato of Naha Okinawa. At Okinwan Karate-Do & Kobudo Academy you will find a family oriented modern facility with classes for children and adults of all ages. Classes are broken up into age and rank so that all students receive the best instruction available. Children's classes focus on developing self esteem, self control, and a positive attitude that they can carry with them throughout life. Adult classes focus on the same principles as well as physical conditioning and self defense skills, along with many other concepts. Our goals are to give each student the opportunity to accomplish anything they want. We give them the key and they open the door. Our instructors are here to guide them on their way. Karate is a journey that never ends. It is a slow and winding road with peaks and valleys. For those who choose to travel that road with us, we welcome you along.

The Northern Shaolin Kung Fu Academy is designed for individuals seeking an authentic Kung Fu training experience. Our programs are designed for every skill level, from beginner to mastery. We offer classes for children and adults of all ages.  Our Master, Sifu William Liu, is top-level instructor with years of teaching experience in both China and United States. The term Kung Fu or 'Gong Fu' in Chinese refers to the achievement and excellence that is obtained through the hard work and dedication of training. Through the challenging process of learning Kung Fu, our students experience the physical benefits of the strengthening of their bodies and learning to defend themselves.

Shaolin Kung Fu International (formerly Ben's Shaolin Kung Fu)   was established in 2003 and has been serving the Bay area for over almost 10 years. Shaolin Kung Fu International  is a Chinese Kung Fu education and training institute intends to pass on the knowledge and culture of Shaolin Kung Fu to our students. Our focus is on developing the studentsin all aspects of his/her life. Discipline, respect, confidence, determination, attention to detail and a healthy lifestyle are just some of the aspects developed through Kung Fu/Wushu training. Kung Fu/Wushu training offers a lot of benefits. It not only strengthens your physique but also enhances the quality of life. It can reduce daily stress and improve your health and vitality. For children, Kung Fu/Wushu training helps develop self-discipline, mutal respect and promotes self-esteem. These are all essential to their future success. We are confident that you will enjoy what we have to offer at Shaolin Kung Fu International  and invite you to come and experience our special approach to the Martial Arts.

Our Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu program is composed of a beginner, intermediate, and advanced curriculum making the sport easy to pick up for anybody. The Jiu-Jitsu program involves learning the better parts of Greco-Roman wrestling, Judo, and submission wrestling for a complete feet to floor game. Our Kickboxing program is an awesome workout involving heavy bags, kicking targets, focus gloves, and Thai pads. The Kickboxing class is instructed by professional kickboxing coaches so you will learn perfect technique and avoid injuries as well. The combination of Jiu Jitsu and Kickboxing are perfect for those interested in MMA training. Our Boxing program consists of learning all the fundamentals of the sport. Students learn how to utilize the heavy bag, speed bag, double end bag, as well as the conditioning and footwork needed for sparring in our competition size Boxing ring. Our Kids classes are great for confidence and character development as well as bully busting. Paragon Academy is proud to offer Santa Barbara's only youth mixed martial arts summer camp!

This system is called Street Fighting, it is nothing wild and without form, but in essence it is the complete opposite, it is very discipline oriented and military structured, incorporating traditions, philosophies, theories, concepts, common sense analogies and self-defense aspects of the martial arts.  It is mainly comprised of elements from Jiu-Jitsu, Tae-Kwondo, Kenpo and Streetology.  F.E.K.S. is an institution for higher learning.One going through this systematic art form will cultivate a better living understanding of life in general from the concepts of Yin and Yang, which is the complete in opposites in this universe, learning the kinetics of human functions.  The workout program is very exciting, consisting of warm ups, for the cardio vascular system while listening to music, cadences that helps the military structure, stretching for limbering up, floor exercises dealing with proper falling techniques, Katas, CPR, First Aid, Anatomy, Street Combative Techniques dealing with pressure points and joint locks and cool down exercises for best results and effectiveness.

Our goal is to provide consistent training in the art of Martial Arts with an emphasis on self-defense, character enrichment and life skills. Confidence / Respect / Self-Control / Coordination / Perseverance / Self-Defense / Team Work / Motivation / Mentoring & Leadership / Positive Character Development and Family Unity are developed throughout the program.

Paragon Brazilian Jiu Jitsu San Luis Obispo and Templeton are the premier martial arts training facilities on the Central Coast. Not only offering Brazilian Jiu Jitsu but also traditional Muay Thai kickboxing through the Elite Muay Thai Academy. All classes and training are conducted in 4,000 square foot training facilities. We provide a safe, respectful, family environment by focusing on discipline, fitness, sport, and self-defense training. We have a variety of classes, class times, and two locations to fit your training needs.Our Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu program is composed of a beginner, intermediate, and advanced curriculum making the sport easy to pick up for anybody. The Jiu-Jitsu program involves learning the better parts of wrestling, Judo, and submission wrestling for a complete grappling system.

Our mission is to guide students in a positive direction. In an effort to build camaraderie within our school, we hope to establish a trust between teachers, students, and parents. So that our students, your children, may become MASTERS in all aspects of LIFE.

Thanks for visiting the Twin Dragons Martial Arts website.  Mr Darryl Gallardo has offered instruction in Hapkido/Taekwondo in the Camarillo area for nearly 15 years.  He opened Twin Dragons Mixed Martial Arts with an intention of sharing mixed martial arts with a self-defense focus in March 2009.  He has followed his dream daily teaching people of all ages and skills empowering arts, growing confidence, balance, fitness, and enjoying the arts of performance and competition along the way.

Shotokan-style karate dojo in Merced, CA. S.K.I. Karate Dojo in Merced, CA is owned by Sensei Amilton Barboza.  Sensei Barboza is a 4th degree black belt and has a university teaching credential in Shotokan karate from Long Island University, NY (1994).

The American Taekwondo Association (ATA) is the premier North American organization dedicated to the martial arts discipline of taekwondo, and is the founding organization of other international affiliates that include the World Traditional Taekwondo Union (WTTU)  and the   Songahm Taekwondo Federation (STF).  Counting both the U.S. and worldwide, our organizations have over 1,500 independently owned and operated licensed schools and clubs, and have registered over one million students since the ATA's inception in 1969.Since the first class was taught many years ago, the focus of our program has remained the same: to provide students the highest quality martial arts instruction available in a safe and positive learning environment that people of all ages can enjoy. Our instructors combine excellent student instructor ratios with state of the art training facilities. This has helped establish ATA schools and clubs as the leaders in the martial arts industry. Each instructor is a graduate of an instructor program that represents more than thirty years of research and development. He or she will be with you every step of the way to help you reach your individual goals (and maybe even reach some new goals you never before thought possible).

At Kim's Hapkido, we teach Jang Mu Won Hapkido which was founded by Grandmaster Chong Sung Kim. Jang Mu Hapkido emphasizes timing and precision in the execution of techniques with great devotion to detail. Grandmaster has often stated that the difference between mediocre technique and outstanding, effective technique is paper thin. Jang Mu Won Hapkido teaches techniques that are readily applied by students in any situation.

In 2005 black belt Dave Clahan, decided to open a much-needed East Bay academy for the Ralph Gracie family, choosing Berkeley as the location 
to further spread Gracie Jiu Jitsu in the Bay Area.  With a history of champion black belt head instructors, the Ralph Gracie Berkeley Academy 
has consistently grown since its opening.  Today, the Ralph Gracie Berkeley Academy’s 4,000 square foot facility with 2,000 square foot mat offers over 30 classes per week, including kids and youth classes, judo, boxing, kickboxing, MMA, no-gi, and beginner and advanced jiu jitsu classes.

K-One Fitness offers a variety of programs with something for everyone: fitness boot camps, boxing, sparring, kickboxing (contact & Muay Thai), Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu, Wrestling Take-Downs, MMA Circuit, and Mixed Martial Arts programs for kids.

The Kid Power Martial Arts Studio is part of Sityodtong LA's 7,500 square foot State of the Art training facility that includes top notch training equipment; Zebra brand mats, a professional Boxing ring, a competition size MMA cage, a fully equipped weight room with custom built monkey bars and a full service juice bar. The Kid Power Martial Arts Studio is complete with its own private restroom, heavy bags, a speed bag; Twins brand Thai pads, focus mitts and various size jump ropes to accommodate the different age groups. Our goal is to help children achieve their best through the Martial Arts.  At Kid Power Martial Arts students are taught important leadership skills including respect, self-control, discipline, teamwork and much more . . .

At Dethrone Base Camp, we offer fun, engaging work-outs and the opportunity to develop your skills in a range of martial arts. The disciplines offered include Muay Thai and kickboxing, boxing, wrestling, Brazilian jiu-jitsu, submission grappling and mixed martial arts. We also offer kids MMA where your children will learn how to defend themselves against bullies while earning confidence and discipline. Our staff members are a mix of current and former professional fighters and experts in their individual disciples. You'll learn the correct form in a controlled environment while getting in the best shape of your life. In addition to getting in great shape and learning self-defense, you'll have the opportunity to join one of our competition teams in amateur boxing, amateur MMA, adult Brazilian jiu-jitsu and kids wrestling and jiu-jitsu. Whether your dream is to become a professional MMA fighter or you're looking for great, fun workouts to get in shape, Dethrone Base Camp is the place for you. Visit us today for a complimentary training session and experience the feeling of accomplishment you earn at Dethrone Base Camp.

The main focus of our academy is to impart the Art of Jiu-Jitsu to our students. We also promote the integration of Jiu-Jitsu and Judo techniques and emphasize the physical conditioning of our athletes. We foster a collaborative and team atmosphere on and off our training mat. We welcome everyone, from novice to expert, young to old. All that is truly required is the desire to learn.

Martial Arts USA has been established in Petaluma since 1993, but our lineage dates back to the late 60′s, when Grandmaster Soo Woong Lee came
to the United States. Throughout the years we have been dedicated to helping the community grow through its teaching of martial arts. Our 
school is a 4,000 sqft studio consisting of two training spaces. There is a children’s room and a comfortable sitting area for parents to watch.

Get ready, Lake Forest — the ultimate fitness experience has arrived, located conveniently off the 5 freeway near El Toro Rd and Swartz Dr. This is UFC Gym – the only fitness facility of its kind, and the only one inspired by the world’s absolute undisputed leader in mixed martial arts. Whether it is boxing, kickboxing, jiujitsu or one of the hundreds of classes offered, you are guaranteed a complete workout experience – strengthening and toning while building endurance and functional fitness. We’re proud to offer our members and guests the finest training available, giving individuals of all ages and fitness levels the opportunity to train different than ever before. You'll feel the burn with The Workout™ –an ultra training session, proven to blaze through 800-1,000 calories in a single hour! State-of-the–art equipment for weight training, cardiovascular endurance and more – in a striking facility designed to inspire.

Lightning MMA has one of the most impressive MMA gyms in Orange County. At 3200 square feet the facility is just the right size, large enough to have two classes conducted simultaneously and yet still have the feel of a small, personal, gym. Our gym has a cage for MMA training and more mat space than most gyms in Orange County. Also included are amenities like: shower, changing room, massage room, lounge area, equipment and nutrition shop, and much  more! Although we have high class facilities, our primary focus is always to provide the best instruction possible. In order to get the most out of your training and have a good experience we provide everything you need to get the most out of your workouts.

The International Yoseikan Budo Federation has its headquarters in Torrance, California (south of Los Angeles).Contrary to the norm in the world of martial arts, this federation is a non-profit organization which exists solely to serve its members. In North America, the Federation is managed by Patrick Augé SenseiShihan, technical director.Patrick Auge Sensei began training in Judo in 1962 in France, and later trained in Karate and Aikido with a student of Hiroo Mochizuki. He was active as a Judo competitor until 1970 after which he lived for seven years as the uchideshi of Master Minoru Mochizuki.Patrick Augé Sensei was named the representative of Yoseikan Budo Aikido for North America in 1977. He then founded multiple dojos in the region of Ottawa (Ontario, Canada) with his wife, Kaoru Sugiyama Sensei. He is currently in Los Angeles developing Yoseikan Budo and regularly travels between Canada, the United States and Japan.

VMX GYM is a fitness studio designed for Personal Training, Martial Arts and personalized group fitness. We provide community training for MMA enthusiasts, amateur fighters also group fitness training for adults of all ages, youth classes for 7-13 year olds, and personal training for all comers. At VMX we pride ourselves in our commitment to customized personal training and injury prevention. As a professional athlete and trainer of 18 years VMX owner and operator Vanessa Mariscal is diligent about the success of her members.Whether you’re stepping into a gym for the first time or looking to return to peak shape, we can accommodate you with a holistic, nutrition-based approach to bettering your health and wellness. From Spinning, to Kickboxing, to “Bell Hell”, a Kettle Bell class designed by Vanessa Mariscal, our certified trainers strive to develop the body comprehensively and to ensure your safety and comfort as you realize your body and mind’s true potential.

The Kyokushin Wah School of Karate was founded in 1992 by Sensei Wah. Long before that, and for over more than 20 years sensei Wah has dedicated himself to teaching countless students. It is because of this dedication that the school has flourished and became a community for people of all ages to meet and learn about the Karate way. The Karate Way is not a myth, and its questions are answered, and path unfolds on a daily basis within the walls of the Kyokushin Wah Dojo, to whoever has made the effort and has had the interest in taking that first step.
East Bay Seido Karate is an affiliated branch of the World Seido Karate Organization located in Berkeley, CA. It is a place where men, women and children come to stay in shape and feed their spirit!

Machatz is a fusion of various martial arts, a system that has been developed over twenty-five years, to bring you the most effective training possible. Our system combines the best of Kung Fu, Karate, Aikido, Judo, Wu Shu arts (such as Tai Chi, Wing Chun and Pa Kua), Russian and Israeli defense systems, and Brazilian and Japanese Jiu-Jitsu.Machatz teaches sound principles of self defense. No gimmicks. No fancy moves that look impressive, but turn out to be useless in a real confrontation. We also teach you to control your power, avoiding the potential injuries that are so common at many competitive martial arts schools.
One of the Best Jiu-Jitsu academies in the United States, Lucas Leite is a multi time World Champion who is one of Leo Vieira's competitors

Our mission at Pacific Martial Arts is to help our students build a solid spiritual foundation for any undertaking. Shito Ryu Karate can be a potent addition to your life, regardless of athletic ability or personal goals. We provide a safe, fun atmosphere for kids and adults to learn. While working in a cooperative environment, we attend to the individual needs of each student.

Chinese Kung Fu Development Center is an organization dedicated to the promotion of traditional Chinese martial arts that is also adapted to the needs of modern sports and wellness. Exploration, performance and learning of traditional Chinese martial arts are the key activities of the organization.  Chinese martial arts (“Wushu” in Chinese) are 
characterized with the fine movement of the limbs, body fluids as well as energy meridians.  It is for health, fitness and mind-cultivation. It is not only a sport but also the carrier of the essence of traditional Chinese culture. It helps to establish an active and positive life style, and inspire the realization of an individual’s highest potential. We uphold a harmonious, healthy and happy teaching philosophy. We strive to mobilize the potential of every student to pursue excellence in athletic ability. Our goal is to help our students develop their physical, mental, athletic and social capabilities, enrich their life style and realize the value of life. Our goal: harmony, health and happiness

Kung fu is great for the body, mind, and spirit. Moo Sool Won doesn't just teach you how to fight; it help the individual gain confidence, self esteem, control, discipline, and helps you become a better person. But with bad health, how will it benefit you? Just read our success stories. So come and join us. You won't regret it!

At Pasadena Martial Arts Academy, we believe in seeing the best in our students and giving them the best we have. It is our mission to see every student attain the rank of Black Belt and beyond. Our training is about continual growth and improvement. We seek to capitalize and emphasize those things a student does best, and help them to use those strengths to improve their other abilities.

At Premier Martial Arts Academy (PMAA) we strive to bring the best in martial arts training with over 85 years of combined martial arts experience. Family owned and operated by United States Martial Arts Hall of Fame Inductees, Premier Martial Arts Academy is dedicated to promoting excellence. Our goal is to provide our students with the necessary tools to help them overcome any obstacle they may encounter in the ring, street or classroom. We offer our students a variety of classes which include: Boxing, Muay Thai, Doce Pares, and Submission Wrestling. In addition, we offer a Young Champions Program which we have carefully designed for kids ages 5-12. PMAA is community driven, minded and spirited in the growth of young hearts and minds. Located in the City of Shasta Lake, CA; Premier Martial Arts Academy is home to many families throughout Shasta County and the greater Northern California region. We consider our students family and no one at PMAA stands alone. Whatever your reasons, fitness or self defense, Premier Martial Arts Academy is here and our doors are open.
On a physical level regular Muay Thai training will give you a well-proportioned physique, build stamina and get you in excellent shape.

column1: Young S. Kim's Family Martial Arts Center
column8: Welcome to our center. It is our pleasure to help you find the benefits of Martial Arts training in your life. Unlike the movie-based stereotype, Martial Arts does not revolve around fighting, but is a discipline and a way of life. It enables people of all ages to reach their full potential, both physically and mentaly. At our center, we teach two Korean styles of Martial Arts, Taekwondo and Hapkido, in an organized curriculum and with a caring, enthusiastic attitude. Our center is headed by Grandmaster Young S.Kim, a 9th degree black belt in Taekwondo and Hapkido with over 40 years of teaching experience. Classes are taught personally by Grandmaster Young S. Kim and a staff of trained instructors in a safe and fun environment.The lessons are designed to not only keep you fit, but also to emphasize discipline, respect, teamwork and attitude. Our teaching methods in self-defense are not geared for attack, but for the development of self-control and confidence to improve the "inner" self. We invite you to join us in the journey towards black belt excellence.

column1: Ernie Reyes West Coast World Martial Arts
column8: At Ernie Reyes West Coast World Martial Arts, we are committed: To motivate people to achieve their goals and maintain a healthy lifestyle in an exciting and challenging environment. Ernie Reyes West Coast World Martial Arts offers a variety of Training Programs, store for purchasing of uniforms and training gear, and See Our Media Gallery through our Members Area. For more specific information about Ernie Reyes West Coast World Martial Arts please visit School Instructors pages, or Contact Us directly. Although we honor Martial Arts traditions that go back centuries, we are dynamic and are constantly seeking new and innovative ways to enthuse and excite our students.

Our goal at the Modesto Grappling Club is to offer competitive classes in Grappling, in a fun, safe and friendly environment.  Grappling, also known as Submission Wrestling, is a mixture of various wrestling styles Collegiate Wrestling, Judo, Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu and Sombo).  The goal of the sport is to obtain a submission hold on your opponent using such techniques as chokes, arm-bars, leg-locks, etc.

99 Martial Arts Center is a world-class Kung Fu/Wushu institution that can turn you into a top martial artist. Here at 99 MAC, you will receive the finest instruction in authentic Chinese Kung Fu/Wushu. Our coaches are internationally recognized for their exceptionally high level of attainment in the art and for their many years of experience as top-level coaches here in the US . Our Coaches have won countless national and international champion in the past in Canada , and the United States . They are ready to create their next lineage of students skilled in the traditions of Chinese Martial Arts. It is our goal at 99 Martial Arts Center to preserve and increase awareness of our Kung Fu tradition and to share with the community the values and benefits of Chinese Martial Arts. As such, we provide classes in authentic Chinese Kung Fu within a comprehensive and extensive program for men, women, and children of all ages and initial skill levels. Our goal here at the Center to help boost your children's confidence, learn respect and self-defense. We actively take our children out to local competition and have won countless medals. Many students have graduated and excelled in their lives after the training. Some of them have been accepted by top universities, with the benefits of the trainings they learned at the Center.

Family Martial Arts Center is located in Lake Forest, California and was created fifteen years ago by Grand Master Michael Kim and Master Monica Kim. They both combine more than 60 years of experience teaching martial arts in the United States and Korea and are certified instructors in Taekwondo, Hapkido and Kumdo. Their school mission is to help their students to learn the traditional values of Korean martial arts in a structured yet fun environment, and better themselves every day in their practice and their lives.

Blue Lake Aikido strives to spread the physical and philosophical teachings of the founder of Aikido, Morihei Ueshiba. He believed, and the owners of Blue Lake Aikido believe, that world peace will come about when violence is eliminated. By chosing active non-violence and self-responsibility, students of Blue Lake Aikido will become part of this vision of world peace. We strive together to bring love and light into the world. The Mission of the Blue Lake Aikido Dojo is to create a large community of self-responsible children and adults committed to the practice of Aikido as the Budo that Morihei Ueshiba O'Sensei envisioned for the world.

IMAC Matial Arts is the best academy in the area bar none. No one else can deliver top notch instruction in so many disciplines of martial arts. We have been serving this area since 2002 and have a 3000 sq. ft. state of the art training facility. We welcome everyone to our facility, from the novice with absolutely no training to the season pro’s. We are a family oriented full service self-defense school and fitness center. We offer an unparalleled character enrichment program for children as well as Women’s self defense and Fitness Classes. Our Buena Park, serving Cypress CA martial arts facility is a family friendly academy that offers clean and safe atmosphere. We believe that trained correctly, martial arts are a safe, challenging way to improve your physical and mental being.

San Clemente's premiere martial arts studio.  Serving all of South Orange County.  We offer Taekwondo classes for all ages as well as cardio kickboxing.  Our qualified staff provides exceptional instruction in a safe and fun environment.

At Five Claw Martial Arts, we teach a wide range of students of all ages and abilities.  We individualize the instruction for each student to meet his or her unique goal—whether it be to learn a self-defense art, increase physical fitness, or train as an MMA fighter. We take your training as seriously as you do.

Alliance Krav Maga & CrossFit is Los Angeles' premier facility for functional fitness and practical self-defense. We are the home of the Krav Maga Alliance, teaching self-defense to civilians, military, and law enforcement. We are also CrossFit Culver City, one of the biggest, longest running CrossFit programs in the city. In addition to Krav Maga and CrossFit, we also offer our exclusive StrikeFit™ kickboxing cardio classes, Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu, Kettle Bell classes, Olympic weightlifting classes, and much more! Contact us for a free trial class, and come on in to see for yourself what all the great reviews are saying!
The American Kenpo Jiu Jitsu Academy in Woodland Hills opened in 1990. For over two decades, The Center has been a Martial Arts Education icon in the San Fernando Valley.
Providing World Class Mixed Martial Arts instruction in the City of Buena Park.  Fantastic classes for Adults and Children alike.  Become a PRO, or get in shape.  We have it all.

The IOMASDA studio will help you develop your individual talents fusing age old techniques, with modern self-defense and health understanding. Sensei Reed uses physics and step by step development to clearly demonstrate and teach his unique system. It is the mission of the Iron Octopus Martial Arts Survival Defense Academy to work with dedication in order for you and your loved ones to reach their fullest potential - mentally, physically, socially, academically, [and] emotionally - by teaching all the essential survival skills.

Our classes are taught in a family-oriented atmosphere that provides individualized attention and positive self-esteem. Our program is designed to help children and adults achieve their goals in life.

The Sennin Foundation Center for Japanese Cultural Arts has been offering instruction in traditional Japanese arts under experienced, certified teachers since 1981. Established in California by H. E. Davey Sensei, it presents separate training in Japanese systems of yoga, healing arts, martial arts, and fine arts. Ongoing classes are available to people of all ages and levels of health, including classes for children ages five and up. Members of the Sennin Foundation Center have access to the rich traditions of Japan's cultural arts through practice in the group's classical dojo (literally, "training hall of the Way"). Much more than simply a school or studio, an authentic dojo is a gateway into the timeless realm of Asian art and personal development, allowing members of the Sennin Foundation Center to realize vibrant well-being and longevity. In fact, the word "Sennin" describes the ancient Japanese equivalent of a yogi. The Sennin were known for their high degree of enlightenment, splendid health, and according to some ancient myths, their ability to attain immortality. This same emphasis on spiritual realization and physical fitness is stressed by the Sennin Foundation, thus the use of the term Sennin.
Nemuri Kuma Jujitsu and Fitness is the premier Danzan Ryu Jujitsu dojo in Northern Sacramento. Danzan Ryu Jujitsu is the most widely practiced form of traditional jujitsu in the United States.

Z-Ultimate Self Defense Studios, LLC – ZUSDS – is a part of a family of martial arts companies formed with one goal in mind – to provide “Z-Ultimate” martial arts experience for students and their families by providing life changing and character building experiences through world-class personalized martial arts instruction. It is the largest martial arts company of its kind, with locations in the Midwest and on the West Coast. What is unique about Z-USDS – besides it’s Dynamic Mastery Method™ of instruction – is that it is NOT just an association or license, where any martial artist can pay a small fee and use the rights to the logo and attain certification. There are many such organizations that boast 
hundreds, even thousands of members with this model. With a philosophy of leadership that teaches, “Be a product of what you represent”, every single staff and support member of the Z-USDS family are martial artists and train actively. By doing so, we never are “out of touch” with what is happening in our locations because we are students, too.

Our San Diego Dojo (school) is dedicated to the teaching of Traditional Martial Arts (Budo) in its original, pure form. Budo (Martial Art) is made up of the two words Bu –martial (fighting or self-defense) and Do – the way or path. Bu is the real, practical application of the art and the Do is the mental and spiritual path that the training will take you on. The benefits of learning budo are many. However, the path is a long one and many groups are trying to create a shortcut. There are no ‘shortcuts’ in real Traditional Martial Arts – the path is long because that is the only way to reap the benefits.Budo is a treasure of human culture that has been handed down through hundreds of years as a priceless heritage. This valuable body of knowledge shows us the way to seek perfection of self through physical, mental and spiritual training. It is our responsibility to protect and preserve Budo for future generations.

Shambhala Martial Arts is located in Brea, California, and has been serving the communities of North Orange County since 1995.Our students gather to our Dojang from nearby communities including Fullerton, Yorba Linda, La Habra and Placentia to practice self-defense and Tae Kwon Dofrom Master Yang, a fifth degree black belt. Shambhala students learn about respect and how to make life-enriching decisions that will stay with them through their lifetime.Shambhala Masters dedicate their lives to more than just teaching their students to excel in self-protection. Shambhala Masters also dedicate their lives to continually gaining a greater understanding of the age old wisdom of Shambhala and to share this secret wisdom with their students.

Master Kim and his staff take great pride in the uniqueness and excellence that is TaeKwonDo USA. Established in 2001 and second to none, our school is affiliated with the World Taekwondo Federation (WTF), the American Taekwondo Union (ATU) and the California Taekwondo United (CTU). Taekwondo USA is the ultimate place to dedicate yourself to attaining your personal goals and accomplishments... Perhaps a Black Belt...all within a special community of fellow martial arts students. At TaeKwonDo USA, we are a family.

Classes at the La Palma Community Center started in 2001 and has grown very large since the beginning. The training features an emphasis on personal growth. Students improve physical fitness, achieve mental alertness, reduce stress and gain a positive attitude. Classes consist of stretching, body conditioning, and self-defense techniques such as kicking, blocking, striking, and grappling. Our program is designed for all levels of athleticism and martial arts experience. The training encourages teamwork and personal responsibility in a safe, disciplined and respectful environment. Our training is appropriate for the age of the student and includes limited, controlled physical contact.

Tenri Judo is renowned for their many top-notch judo athletes such as Shinji Hosokawa, a Los Angeles Olympic gold medalist; Tadahiro Nomura, a three time Olympic gold medalist; and Shinichi Shinohara, who won the World Championship in two different weight classes and is the previous head coach of the Japan National Judo Team.The essence and characteristics of Tenri Judo is instilled here at the Los Angeles Tenri Dojo.  Tenri Dojo teaches the importance of developing a sound mind and body and refines the technique of “ippon”.

The purpose of Tiger’s Tae Kwon Do is to develop an individual’s mental and physical well being through a highly stylized and deliberate method of rigorous martial arts training. The result of this training is an empowering sense of self-worth, and the ability to control one’s physical state and personal destiny. At Tiger’s Tae Kwon Do, our students come first. Our goal is to help each and every student achieve the many benefits that martial arts has to offer. At Tiger’s Tae Kwon Do, we are not only interested in fighting skills but also in the development of the person as a whole. These are the tools of everyday life; what you learn here, you can apply at home, at work and at school. Higher self-esteem, more confidence and better physical health are things you can use everyday and everywhere. The main goal at Tiger’s Tae Kwon Do is self-improvement. We set physical goals in Tae Kwon Do that challenge your inner self to carry you onward to achieve the goal of self-improvement. From the very beginning of training, self-control, confidence and self-discipline are stressed as the real goals of training.

You will learn to defend against attackers with and without weapons. You will learn to defend against real-life modern day fighting styles and attacks. You will learn the foundational principles and forms of Kung Fu and using your attacker’s energy & motion against them. You will learn to react with your skills naturally and at lightning speed. you will learn Qigong and iron palm, you will learn to understand the word "Honor" and Inner peace. You will learn to be the"Calm of the Storm".
If you're searching for an exciting way to boost your child's confidence, fitness and self-discipline, you can trust Chozen San Dimas Karate to give you the results you seek!

I open up the school in Stockton, Ca. in 1986. We belong to the Chinese combat union, certified school in wing Chun or Young Chaun Quan. We do not carry belts at our school so there are no belt fees. You receive certificates of levels earned by training not by paying. This way it’s more rewarding, because you trained hard to earn them, however there is no pressure you train at your own pace.

A family-oriented martial arts school teaching Kung Fu and Tai Chi. Our curriculum includes empty-hand styles, animal styles, weapon training, and acrobatic tumbling. Classes available for children ages 2+ and adults.
In  Pulido's Pro-fitness we also offer classes for Tae Kwon Do, kickboxing, Muay Thai and stick fighting. Instructor GM Pulido 16 world time world Champion.

Kyoshi-Shihan Shoji Nishimura is the chief karate instructor of USA Wado-ryu Karate-do Renmei in California.  He has over 40 years experience in Karate and holds 7th degree black belt. USA Wado-Ryu Karate-do Renmei has three easy to reach locations in Orange County, California.  The main Dojo or Instruction center is in  Laguna Niguel with other classes located in  Huntigton Beach and Torrence.

Traditional Aikido of Sonoma offers a rare opportunity to study and train O'Sensei Morihei Ueshiba's Aikido. Ian Noel Kennedy 5th dan and Nathan Feileacan 3rd dan are the chief instructors.  Paul Olszewski 2nd dan runs the kids aikido progam on Sundays. Classes in this form of self defense are ongoing, and offered in a non-competitive atmosphere for all ages.

Alameda Aikikai offers beginning through advanced classes in aikido, weapons, Iaido, as well as  Zazen meditation.Teacher training program is available if interested. Alameda Aikikai was established by Mike Flynn, Shihan in January 1991 and is affiliated with   Birankai North America established by T.K. Chiba, Shihan. Chief Instructor Elmer Tancinco, 5th degree black belt, Shidoin, studied directly under Mike Flynn, Shihan. He is also a graduate of the Kenshusei program, a rigorous teacher training program for dedicated practitioners of the art who are devoted to transmitting and preserving aikido. He has taught at National Universities, and taught seminars in United Kingdom, Portugal, Australia.

Classes are offered through the City of Riverside Park & Recreations. Sensei Hung is a Shan-dan in Shotokan karate. She has been involved in karate for several years as a competitor, instructor, and referee. Sensei still competes locally, nationally, and internationally, and has placed in several tournaments around the globe. Mission Statement: to educate children through an activity promoting discipline, confidence, responsibility, and self defense.

Nicky's Pro Karate Mixed Martial Arts Fighting System is a combination of Boxing, Muay Thai, Tae Kwon Do, traditional Karate, submission grappling and Bulgarian Military Hand-to-Hand combat (SRB) organized in a progressive, battle tested curriculum with the prime goal being body/mind development and self-discovery. Established in 2002, Nicky's Pro Karate has been dedicated to shaping the successful lives of hundreds of families in Calabasas and the surrounding areas.  This 11-year commitment to being the best in Martial Arts training has resulted in a sterling reputation for owner, Nikolay Sartchadjiev (Master Nicky), and his motivated staff.  Nicky's Pro Karate is the premier Mixed Martial Arts Studio in the West San Fernando Valley.

The Health and Karate Center is a family martial arts program and is built around attitudes of peace and balance, safety, and respect. We ask that these be the first and foremost goals that you strive for in pursuing martial arts training. Located in Humboldt County, California, we provide the most effective health and safety guidance available with the most positive and user-friendly training. Here at the Health and Karate Center, we train in a unique and flexible system allowing you to benefit from the energy of everyone working toward a similar goal. This means you may attend most of our classes with no additional cost and on whatever schedule works for you. Each of the programs at the Health and Karate Center is aimed at rapid, yet realistic, progress. You will not finish looking or feeling like you did when you started.

Martial Arts America is the largest group of professional martial arts  schools in the world.  Founded on the principles of teaching excellence, personal attention and tradition, we provide you with the most complete and effective methods to reach your full potential. At Martial Arts America, our instructors are personally selected, not only for their martial arts skills, but also for their ability to effectively communicate their knowledge and understanding to students of all ages.  Through a special company sponsored program of advanced training they are continuously upgrading their skills.  It is no surprise that Martial Arts America instructors are ranked among the finest in the world. At Martial Arts America we are interested not only in self defense skills, but also in the complete personal development of each student.  Individual attention is a feature of each and every class, allowing Martial Arts America students to progress quickly and easily toward their personal goals.  Our instructors take seriously their responsibility as role models for younger students, teaching them the importance of strong character, leadership and good values.

Classes at Karate Kids focus on developing RESPECT, FOCUS, and COURAGE…all the skills our kids need to take care of themselves one day. We also offer more classes for more age groups than any martial arts school in town. That’s because we teach children only! We are the experts in teaching children karate.

column1: Stephen J. Amsler's Martial Arts Center
column8: Stephen Amsler and staff have been professionally teaching Taekwondo in Orange County, CA for over 22 years. We are dedicated to helping children and adults develop confidence through the study of martial arts. Master Amsler provides all of our students with a Taekwondo Curriculum Book and DVD so that you can train at home as well as in class. Our qualified Black Belt instructors are energetic and outgoing. They have advanced training and continue to upgrade their skills. They also have a sincere interest in helping you reach your physical and mental goals.

We offer classes in Traditional and Olympic style of Tae Kwon Do, weapons as well as a Mix Martial Art of Hap Ki Do self defense Techniques that consist of locking, throwing, summision and escaping techniques from different positions. In addition through our Martial Arts Classes we teach Discipline, Respect, Courtesy, Integrity, Perseverance, Self Control, Self Defense and Morals as part of character building. Our children's classes help our students to keep active and focus in their schoolwork and at home. IN today's society not only is it profitable for our chldren to know how to defend themselfves and how to avoid dangerous situations, it's a necessity. Our adult's classes help our students to build up their physical conditioning and endurance. It has improved their reaction, coordination,flexibility, and level of confidence. It is great for weight loss and helps relieve stress and tension.  It is also great for adults that are looking for something positive to invest their time and energy into.

Vision Martial Arts specializes in Kids Martial Arts, and Adult Martial Arts.  Our training programs are comprehensive and balanced and offer students the ability to learn technique, strength, self-confidence, self-esteem, and self-defense.   At Vision Martial Arts we want our students to feel comfortable in class and to really get the most out of 
their time spent here.  Individuals will practice, progress, and accomplish while training here at our San Jose Martial Arts facility.

Miller's ATA Black Belt Academy offers fun-filled, action packed classes for all ages!  Find out why Taekwondo is the most popular martial art in the world! Miller's ATA Black Belt Academy has been in Marin County for over twenty years and is dedicated to giving you and your family an exciting experience.

The vision of West Coast Krav Maga is to build a community by helping people get in shape, be safe and at the same time instill the life skills and character of a true martial artist. We will also help you achieve self discipline, high self esteem, a positive out look, a spirit of constant improvement, and an attitude that refuses to give up. These values and life skills will lead to remarkable improvements in academics, careers, and relationships, literally making a better community one black belt at a time.
